beers.description: So you thought West Coast IPA was dead? Well, guess what? It's baaaaaaaack! You better brace yourself for the zombie hop-apocalypse! Sorta Mostly Dead is a venerable undead army hopped with Citra, Mosaic Cryo, and Strata that brings it with a super dank profile of dense oily lupulin, grapefruit zest, fruity pebbles, fresh pine, blueberries, herbaceous nugs, and fresh melon! Is it... adeptly bitter? appropriately dry? clean finish? brilliantly clear coppery hue? Yes, yes, yes, and YES! The dead rises again!!!

beers.name: International-Style Juice
beers.description: A one-off collaboration between Reuben's and our friends at Alvarado Street

beers.name: Galaxy, Nelson Guide Post
beers.description: At Trillium, we're committed to our New England roots through the support of local agricultural systems. Whenever possible, we look to source products grown by nearby suppliers. We've also fostered relationships with suppliers producing some incredibly high quality ingredients all over the world. With Guide Post, we're bridging the gap by combining our favorite raw ingredients from both here and there, with the goal of presenting something that is singular, yet representative of each originating location.For the first interpretation of Guide Post, we've constructed a grist bill packed with New England-grown grain, malted in Hadley, MA by our dear friends at Valley Malt. Crafted just 100 miles from our brewery, their grain lays the framework for hand-selected lots of two intensely aromatic hop varieties, Australian Galaxy and New Zealand Nelson Sauvin. Guide Post opens with intermingling notes of overripe pineapple and gooseberry, followed by a charge of white grape must and fresh cut grass. Vivid and juicy, with a pleasantly dry finish, Guide Post is a delicious homage to our suppliers.

beers.name: Citra, Simcoe Guide Post
beers.description: For the second interpretation of Guide Post we selected ingredients from both near and far that we've developed a deep appreciation for throughout the years. Wyermann® Pilsner malt is a standout amongst 2-row base barley malt. Utilized in beers such as Vicinity, this continental German malt enhances both body and mouthfeel in the finished beer, setting the stage for two hops that represent substantial leaps forward in American hop breeding: Citra and Simcoe.

beers.name: Steve-Fu!
beers.description: For our 600th batch, we present to you a very special collaboration with our friends at Fidens. On a trip out to Cali, love was found between a man and his west coast ipa, so we could not think of a better way to commemorate our love of West Coast IPA and our buds from Albany than to brew up a crispy, clean and flavor packed beer affectionately named "Steve-Fu!". Our latest Triple Dry Hopped West Coast India Pale Ale is jam packed with Citra Incognito, Citra, Chinook, Amarillo, Strata, Strata CGX, Mosaic, Simcoe and Freestyle Nelson. Bright notes of ripe citrus, wild blueberries, juicy strawberry and resiny pine overwhelm the senses, while the finish is beautifully dry with a delicately assertive bitterness.

beers.name: The Dank Don't Die
beers.description: After a long and dangerous journey full of danktifying terrors, the NPBC crew, armed only with Cyro Hops and a Mash Paddle, made their way back from their ultimate mission: Create The DANKEST IPA Collaboration Ever Assembled, with their homies at Cellarmaker. With a hop bill that includes Nectaron, Citra, Galaxy, Citra Cryo, & Nelson Sauvin, the dank are most definitely alive and walking the streets.

beers.name: Disciples of Fu! Masters of Mosaic
beers.description: The Disciples of Fu! Masters of Mosaic is the next iteration in a series of single-hopped beers featuring the hops used to make Hop-Fu! We’re returning back to Mosaic to bring a whole new level of hop mastery. Loaded with notes of ripe blueberry, juicy mango, and tropical guava, this single-hop stunner will kick you right in the tastebuds and leave your palate stunned.

beers.name: Dankers Hill
beers.description: Our second taproom location in Bankers Hill has been open for 7 months now and what better way to celebrate than with a fresh batch of its commemorative beer? Dankers Hill is a DDH West Coast IPA, brewed with stacks on stacks of Centennial, Mosaic, Citra, Simcoe, and Strata hops to offer a new-money take on a classic style. With notes of citrus rind, juicy blueberry, and dank resin, this 7.4% sipper finishes dry and crisp. Our Bankers Hill location is open and thriving, and we hope to see you there soon with this tasty sipper.

beers.name: Green Rush Fresh Hop IPA
beers.description: Every September brings the Green Rush: the annual influx of brewers and beer lovers to the Yakima Valley to search out the best fresh hops. We've got a front row seat on our family hop farm, and this year, we've again partnered with the legendary Russian River Brewing Company to create a fresh hop IPA that tastes like striking gold - fresh hop gold, that is. This fresh hop West Coast IPA features freshly picked homegrown Simcoe® hops for vibrant aromas of grapefruit, peach, mango, and resin.

beers.name: Smiley Eyes
beers.description: The sun is shining, the flowers are in bloom, and Smiley Eyes is here! We collaborated with our buds at Everywhere Beer to bring you this absolutely delightful DDH West Coast IPA. At 7.5% and packed with Nelson, Citro, Riwaka, and Southern Cross hops, Smiley Eyes is like a ray of sunshine in a glass. Bursting with juicy flavors of ripe apricot, peach ring gummies, and tangy ruby red grapefruit, it's without a doubt guaranteed to brighten up any day. Get ready to be whisked away on a whimsical flavor journey with each sip of this bright and flavorful springtime sipper!

beers.name: The Final Death
beers.description: Get ready, fighters! We teamed up with the fierce folks at Wondrous Brewing to bring you The Final Death. This DDH West Coast IPA is mega-dank with a crisp finish, leaving you feeling like an absolute winner. One sip will have you saying, “That was great! Super! Excellent!"

beers.name: NPBC7 DDH West Coast IPA
beers.description: NPBC7 Double Dry Hopped West Coast India Pale Ale hopped with ludicrous amounts Chinook, Citra Incognito, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, NZ Hops Nectaron & Nectaron Cryo, Citra, Simcoe and Freestlye Peacharine. Dank, dense and dieselly on the nose with mouth watering tasting notes of citrusy orange, wild blueberries and juicy peach leading to a deliciously dry finish complimented by a present, but delicate bitterness.

beers.name: Crown-Fu!
beers.description: Did you hear the good news? We’ve got a new spot opening in Crown Point, and we couldn’t think of a better way to mark the occasion than with the release of Crown-Fu! West Coast IPAs are no jesting matter around here, and we certainly followed the royal protocol when triple dry-hopping this gem with the finest Citra, Amarillo, Mosaic, Simcoe, Chinook, Columbus, and Peacharine found in this fair kingdom. It doesn’t get more aromatic than this: think stone fruit, ripe pineapple, and a dash of pine. Take a swig and let saturated strawberry, red fruit, dank guava, and pine resin wash over your palate. Get ready to swing by our new digs and pull up a chair, we can’t wait to share a Crown-Fu! with you as soon as our doors open!

beers.name: NPBC8 TDH West Coast IPA
beers.description: We couldn’t celebrate our anniversary without a special West Coast IPA release! Now we proudly present NPBC8, TDH West Coast IPA. We put Krush (formerly known as HBC-586), Columbus, Citra, Mosaic, Amarillo, & Strata to the test, and boy, do they shine! True to its style, this one is carefully layered with flavor upon flavor, and complimented by a satisfyingly dry texture and prominent bitterness. Ruby red grapefruit, fresh blueberry, sticky P.O.G. juice, and dank pine resin are all wrapped up in each sip.

beers.name: Sam-Fu!
beers.description: It has been an honor for us to get to know, pour at their festivals, make beer and most importantly become friends with all the amazing humans at Other Half, so in our own way we hope to pay our respects to one of the pioneers of craft beer, Sam, with our latest Double Dry Hopped West Coast India Pale Ale, Sam-Fu!. Hopped with a wild amount of Indie Chinook, Columbus Cryo, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, Mosaic Incognito, NZ Hops Nectaron Cryo and Freestyle Nelson Sauvin, this beer is bursting with crazy amounts of sticky dankness on the nose accompanied by luscious tasting notes of juicy blueberry, resinous pine, ripe cantaloupe and wild, red strawberries that is closed out by a beautifully dry finish and a wonderfully assertive bitterness.

beers.name: The Coast With the Most
beers.description: West Coast! West Coast! West Coast! It’s the Coast with the Most, babe. This West Coast IPA was double dry-hopped with Citra DynaBoost, Citra, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, and Simcoe, offering notes of ripe berries, juicy stone fruit, and a subtle dankness. If you say it three times, it might just appear in your glass. It’s worth a try, at least.

beers.name: Stratacadabra
beers.description: Alakazam! Hocus Pocus! Shazam! Presto Change-o! Stratacadabra?!? Before you know it, this fresh DDH West Coast IPA will have you saying some fancy wizarding words! We assembled a magical trio of Strata, Citra, and Nelson Sauvin hops to enchant your palate with flavors of sauvignon blanc, gooseberries, white gummy bears, grapefruit, fresh pine forest, and a dash of the stickiest nugs. Clean, clear, dry, bitter? You bet!

beers.name: Memento Mori
beers.description: We brewed a collaboration beer for the synth-pop legends Depeche Mode to celebrate the release of their new album and tour! Memento Mori, the album, just debuted recently, so we’re doing our first release of this beer to coincide. This 7% West Coast IPA was double dry-hopped with YCH Trial 303 Cryo, Citra Incognito, Simcoe Cryo, Mosaic, Citra, Simcoe, & Cashmere hops to offer vibrant notes of ripe stone fruit, citrus rind, and subtle pine. After a single sip, you just can’t get enough.

beers.name: Mess With the West, Die Like the Rest
beers.description: The Fu! Crew just won’t stop brewing those deader-than-dead West Coast IPAs, so off to detention they go. Between rounds of hangman and shooting spitballs at each other, Kelsey passed a note to the rest of the brew team and what do you know - another recipe for a new DDH West Coast IPA! They packed their backpacks full of Amarillo, Citra, Mosaic & Simcoe and put the hops to work, creating a beer with big grapefruit peel and subtle pine aromas, followed by tropical orange, mango, and slight berry flavors. Take note, the Fu! Crew’s message is loud and clear: Mess with the West, Die like the Rest!

beers.name: Saturated Substance
beers.description: We pulled out our hazmat suits and paired up with fellow scientists from Von Ebert Brewing to concoct a DDH West Coast IPA that made our Geiger counter go haywire. While we thought about throwing some glow stick liquid (or perhaps Plutonium?) into the kettle, we decided to hop this nuclear brew into oblivion with a trifecta of Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo & Mosaic 702. Aromas of big blueberry and red berry carry through on the sip to mingle with piney floral flavors, while an assertive, sticky bitterness, and robust mouthfeel radiate throughout the drinking experience. Suit up - hop meltdown incoming!

beers.name: Dead As A Doornail
beers.description: Here lies another truly, unequivocally dead West Coast IPA, Dead as a Doornail. Beloved beer, survived by Simcoe, Citra, Mosaic, Nelson Sauvin, and Nectaron layered six feet deep. We’ll remember it as wonderfully aromatic with dense peach, passion fruit, and pine, and flavors of overripe stone fruit, crisp white grape, and a dry, lightly dank finish. Our condolences to the other beers in your fridge - you’ll be reaching for this one first.

beers.name: Brewer's Delight
beers.description: I said-a hip, hop, the hoppy, the hoppy to the Citra hop-a you don't stop dry-hoppin’. Brewer's Delight brings you the whole gang of Citra, Citra Incognito, and Citra Cryo along to show off notes of dank pine, pink grapefruit, lime zest, and fresh lemon. So throw your hands high in the air, this Unfiltered DDH IPA will have ya rockin' to the beat without a care.

beers.name: Denny Kong
beers.description: Power up and grab your mash paddle! Home Brew Con is here in San Diego, so we teamed up with a whole slew of buds to bring this commemorative beverage, Denny Kong. The iconic hosts of the Experimental Brewing podcast collabed with us to bring you a DDH West Coast IPA that takes your taste buds on an adventurous odyssey. Sponsored by Yakima Chief Hops, BSG, & Wyeast, this beer conquers boundaries, pushing the limits of a classic style and have you feeling ready to leap over barrels and climb up to the brewdeck!

beers.name: The Last Drive-In
beers.description: It’s great. Couldn’t find it on the app so created it. This place rocks

beers.name: Lucent Realms
beers.description: Hazy, smooth with an earthy flavor

beers.name: Community Guidelines
beers.description: A toast to every brewery who has had their post removed for no good reason by an algorithm. Because we all need some clarity on the matter, we had to brew up a crystal clear DDH West Coast IPA and to make things even more simple, we used only Mosaic hops in the brew. Dank, piney and resiny notes permeate the nose, while delicious notes of blueberry, mixed red berry and subtle citrus console your taste buds each time you have to repost to your account. We are all in this together and we encourage everyone to brew this beer so we can make it a thing because we set our own community guidelines in the craft beer industry!

beers.name: Experimental-Fu!
beers.description: We’re tossing convention aside and whipping up a brand spankin’ new West Coast IPA that’s sure to please! This can only mean one thing: Experimental-Fu! Batch 001 is here! This time we’re putting Nelson Sauvin to the test alongside our tried-and-true Chinook, Citra, Amarillo, Mosaic, & Simcoe. Bright tangerine and pineapple aromas leap out of the glass while tangy white grape, red berry & dank flavors lead into a perfectly crisp finish. This one passes the test with flying colors!

beers.name: Hopewell Manor
beers.description: Welcome, foolish mortals, to Hopewell Manor. With our fellow hosts Troon Brewing, we invite you to take a tour of the brewery barn and step inside the throneroom if you dare, as we declare West Coast IPA king! Loaded with Citra, Eclipse, Rakau, Simcoe & Waimea, this DDH West Coast IPA is not one to miss. Pine resin and ruby red grapefruit notes hit like a lightning bolt, while mandarin peel, apricot, and tangerine dance on the palate before a frightfully dank, dry, and moderately bitter finish. We hope you’ll visit Hopewell Manor again soon, we’re dying to have you.

beers.name: Blossoming Down Under
beers.description: Southern Hemisphere Style IPA with rotating hopsBatch 1 - 3/08/17 - Vic Secret (Draft)Batch 2 - 3/24/17 - Vic Secret, Galaxy and Sauvignon Blanc grape juice (Draft and Canned)Batch 3 - 5/27/17 - Vic Secret, Galaxy, EnigmaBach 4 - 7/02/17 - Australian Enigma and Melba and New Zealand RakauBatch 5 - 9/18/17 - Vic Secret, Galaxy, Nelson with Sauvignon Blanc and Chardonnay JuiceBatch 6 - 10/24/17 - Galaxy and Chardonnay JuiceBatch 7 - Kohatu, Nelson, Galaxy, Sauv Blanc JuiceBatch 8 - Nelson, Enigma, Motueka, Sauv Blanc JuiceBatch 9 - Vic Secret, Galaxy, Enigma and Australian Sauv Blanc JuiceBatch 10 - Vic Secret, Galaxy and Summer with Chardonnay and Sauv Blanc grape juicesBatch - 11 Australian Summer and Enigma Hops and New Zealand Rakau with Australian Chardonnay and Sauvignon Blanc Grape JuiceBatch - 12 Vic Secret & Kohatu and Sauvignon Blanc Juice (Canned)Show Less

beers.name: The Fu! Crew
beers.description: Our beer wouldn’t be quite what it is without The Fu! Crew! Our talented team of brewers has brought home a slew of prestigious awards, so it felt fitting to honor them with a beer. Brewed with Mosaic, Strata, and McKenzie hops, our brewers Zach, John, and Tyson each selected a favorite hop to contribute to this beer. Each sip of this crisp DDH Unfiltered West Coast IPA will offer notes of juicy citrus, mixed berries, and a touch of woody pine. So cheers to The Fu! Crew for holding it down in the brewhouse!

beers.name: Infernal Combustion
beers.description: Risen again, the dead have brought forth a double dry hopped west coast IPA with Citra, Nelson Sauvin, and Nectaron hops. Intense aromas of pineapple, passionfruit, pine, white grapes, lime, and some danky diesel.

beers.name: 15 Speed
beers.description: A clean, crispy DDH West Coast IPA collab! Citra 702, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, Simcoe & Amarillo form the peloton of 15 Speed. Aromatic pine and ripe citrus waft from the glass upon pouring, while flavors of fresh orange, mango and pine tantalize the taste buds. Collaboration with BLAH Brewing for Blind Lady Ale House's 15th Anniversary.

beers.name: Forever In Style
beers.description: Some things just never go out of style... Chuck Taylors, Levi's Jeans, Hard Rock, and Dank AF West Coast IPAs! We joined forces with our old pal Julian Shrago of Beachwood Brewing to create this dank masterpiece. We pushed the malt off to the side and kept this one squarely focused on the hops. Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, and Simcoe? Obviously bruh! But what about some Pahto and Pahto Cryo? What's Pahto, you ask? Well, it just so happens to be a total piney and dank beast of a hop! We topped it all off with a big charge of Strata, you know... for good measure. The result is a balance of passion fruit, evergreen forest, and righteous dankness with some undertones of blueberry and grapefruit zest. Delicious, dry, and dank! What more could you ask for? Get it!

beers.name: Rouge Et Mosaique!
beers.description: Dry Hopped with a new french varietal Barbe Rouge and smoothed over with dank mosaic, this hazy garçon bursts with red-ripe strawberries, raspberries and blueberries.

beers.name: Apparition
beers.description: The first rendition of Apparition was crafted back when we were all still brewing in converted 10 gallon mash tun cooler, first dubbed Mosalaxy. A light grain bill is fed with ample dosings of Galaxy and Mosaic in the whirlpool and dry hop. We are getting huge tropical aromas followed by notes of ripe melon, pineapple, and fresh squeezed orange juice.

beers.name: Beyond Repair
beers.description: Riwaka IPA DDH with Riwaka

beers.name: Disciples of Fu! - Simcoe Syndicate
beers.description: Disciples of Fu! - Simcoe Syndicate is the 3rd in our series of single hopped beers featuring the hops used to make Hop-Fu! This one is stuffed full of Simcoe hops!! We dosed the kettle with plenty of Simcoe Resinate and Simcoe Cryo, then we double dry hopped it with Simcoe and more Simcoe Cryo! The aroma is erupting with pine, Valencia orange zest, passion fruit, and the dankest oily hop resins. Pine forward, firm bitterness, and orangey citrus hoppy flavors completely delights the palate. Bright, clean, crisp and a dry finish will have you revisiting many, many times.

beers.name: A Pale Green Horse
beers.description: A Pale Green Horse is a Kviek IPA brewed with well water, Pale Moon malt from Blacklands, raw wheat and oats from Barton Springs Mill, and Galaxy, Citra, and Mosaic hops. It was dry hopped with Strata, Galaxy, Citra, and Mosaic hops at a rate of 3 lbs. per barrel. We brewed A Pale Green Horse with Brandon Jones of Yazoo when he visited us for an early December Jester King SPON Day. Brandon is a fan of the Hornindal Kveik yeast strain from Omega Yeast Labs, which we used for fermentation. Although it is monoculture, the farmhouse origin of Kviek yeast just makes sense. Not to mention it ferments with flavor fit for a great Hazy IPA.

beers.name: Rye da Tiger
beers.description: A double rye IPA dedicated to a man that made the world a better place. In magic, Three Floyds.

beers.name: Devil's Triangle
beers.description: A Rye IPA with Nelson Hops

beers.name: Thank You, Russell!
beers.description: Many of you know Russell as the sexy dude with a bow-tie calmly navigating the dining room and bar at Brick Farm Tavern, implacable and unflappable even under the busiest conditions. He's become a very close friend of ours over the last year so it is with great remorse that we have to wish him farewell at the beginning of February as he embarks on his next journey. In anticipation of that we gave him free rein over this recipe and he decided he wanted a rye-heavy IPA. We are so happy with his decision! He then selected his favorite hops and given how singular this occasion is we decided to make it even more special by adding them in the largest quantities that we've done to date, 8.5#/ bbl. Woah! Once you taste it I think you'll be thanking Russell too :)

beers.name: Photo System
beers.description: We teamed up with the NERDS at Drownlands Brewery and created a beautifully executed rye DIPA with malted rye, rye flakes, oats and wheat. Double dry-hopped with Cashmere, Motueka and Zappa. Rye spice, strawberry, kiwi-lime and mouthfeel for years.

beers.name: Rye IPA
beers.description: For this beer, we took our regular IPA and added rye to the grain bill. The result is a peachy, tropical, and citrusy juice bomb with a uniquely zesty and slightly spicy rye character.

beers.name: Radio Swan
beers.description: Made with El Dorado and Mosaic hops.

beers.name: Switch Lanes
beers.description: Rye NEIPA dry hopped with Mosaic and Idaho 7

beers.name: Nelson
beers.description: IT'S NELSON OR NOTHINGNamed after Nelson Sauvin, an outstanding hop varietal from New Zealand. The hop is introduced through the brewing and dry-hopping of this complex and well-balanced IPA. A hazy straw hued ale, Nelson is topped by bright white beer foam and offers a tropical hop aroma. The pine and fruity hop notes linger, but are well-balanced by the smooth, malty addition of European rye malts. Enjoy this stunning and multifaceted, yet mellow IPA.

beers.name: Creative Flow
beers.description: Double Rye NEIPA with Galaxy and Falconer's Flight hops

beers.name: Skeleton Revival
beers.description: Hazy Rye IPA with El Dorado and Mosaic hops. No Lactose.

beers.name: Green Dragon
beers.description: Rye IPA DDH with Nelson Sauvin and Southern CrossCan Release 10/21 - 4-pack/$19Nelson Sauvin is one of our favorite hop varieties thanks to its distinct contribution of white wine and gooseberry aromatics. Sometimes it needs a partner though, so we paired it with Southern Cross, another New Zealand-grown variety. It's a combination suggested by science because the signature thiol in Nelson Sauvin (3S4MP) acts synergistically with the apricot-leaning ester from Southern Cross (2MIB).¹Cheers,Mike & Scott1.Takoi, K., Degueil, M., Shinkaruk, S., Thibon, C., Kurihara, T., Toyoshima, K., Tominaga, T. (2009). Specific Flavor Compounds Derived from Nelson Sauvin Hop and Synergy of these Compounds. BrewingScience,Batch #1 - 6.6%Batch #2 - 6.3%

beers.name: Third Rye Blind
beers.description: Double Dry-Hopped Rye Double IPA w/ Hallertau Blanc, Simcoe and Citra hops.

beers.name: Positive Launch
beers.description: Rye IPA brewed with Idaho 7, Amarillo & El Dorado.

beers.name: 37 Pieces of Flair
beers.description: 37 Pieces of Flair is our Golden Rye IPA brewed with Rye from one of our favorite European Maltsters and hopped 100% with our hand-selected Citra

beers.name: Pastrami On Rye
beers.description: "Pastrami on Rye" is an Unfiltered Imperial Rye IPA brewed with Strata, Moutere, and Southern Passion. Dripping with spicy, juicy flavors, this "classic sandwich" utilizes Flaked Rye and Oats for a soft, silky mouthfeel. This intriguing hop blend creates a dank aroma of pineapple, OG Kush, and red currants with a hint of coconut. Think Katz's pastrami, Russian dressing, and seeded mustard on Jewish rye.

beers.name: Hail Santa
beers.description: Our annual tribute to that jolliest of dark overlords. Brewed with local wildflower honey, malted rye, and a touch of light caramel malt. Dry hopped with the classic Cascade and our forever favorite Simcoe. Hail Santa! Notes of Meyer lemon zest, pineapple sage, white flowers, unripe peach, and bergamot. 6.4% ABV.

beers.name: Hype Towel
beers.description: Hype Towel is made using Rye Malt and Patagonia Extra Pale Malt, then hopped with Centennial and Simcoe on the hot side, and then dry hopped with Simcoe, Citra and Mosaic. Tastes is resinous with stone fruit, pine and grapefruit character and a little bit of spice. Soft and juicy as always. Super hype. Towel swinging.

beers.name: Broken Shadows
beers.description: This autumnal miracle was brewed with flaked rye & rye malt, which combine with a profusion of Strata, Crystal, Chinook, and Galaxy hops to yield a profile replete with orange citrus & strawberry, with a hint of spice from the rye and a smooth, creamy mouthfeel. It’s a ridiculously ideal beer for the fall season, although we’d be down to drink it pretty much whenever.

beers.name: Chemical Connection
beers.description: A New England Style IPA brewed with a heavy hand of Rye. The distinct graininess and spice of the rye mingles with a large addition of Idaho 7 and Chinook hops to create tropical flavors as well as pine and black tea flavors.

beers.name: Red's Rye IPA (Bourbon Barrel Aged)
beers.description: It’s Red’s Rye, aged 4 months in 10-year oak bourbon barrels.

beers.name: Jam
beers.description: Hazy, soft IPA brewed with Rye and very healthy dose of Vic Secret.

beers.name: Barrel-Aged 20th Anniversary Ale
beers.description: Imperial Rye IPA aged in rye whiskey Barrels

beers.name: Temporarily Permanent
beers.description: DDH West Coast Rye IPA w/ @freestylehops Nelson hops! // Our Lead Brewer Ian from our Costa Mesa spot dreamt this one up, as a nod to the legendary the OG Alpine Nelson that we all fell in love with years ago. Sitting on a simple bed of Pilsner and Rye Malt, the hops are wonderfully expressive with all the New Zealand love we could ask for. Tasting notes? Think NZ Sauv Blanc, Cotton Candy, Orange Blossom, and pink grapefruit.

beers.name: Old Money
beers.description: Hazy Rye IPA with an all Mosaic dry hop.

beers.name: Currency
beers.description: Rye IPA dry hopped with Denali, Apollo, Ekuanot and 007. Its bursting with dollars and scents. Brewed with our Long Island brothers Barrier.

beers.name: Thanks Obama
beers.description: Thanks Obama is a Winter Rye IPA that features a new, experimental hop variety (06297, if you’re curious). Expect a complex, spicy malt character with candied grape and vanilla cream hop aromas. Add a little honey and malt sweetness to round it out, and there you go. It checks in at 6.5% ABV, and will be the perfect beer to inaugurate your next visit to the Beer Hall. Reflect on the last eight years, look to the future, and enjoy a pint with your fellow Americans.

beers.name: Morph - Batch #26
beers.description: Rotating IPA Series: 5/2/16 recipe is a rye IPA featuring Ella and Azacca hops; ripe cantaloupe aroma; crisp rye spiciness and a lingering resinous finish

beers.name: Double Dry-Hopped Citra Legacy
beers.description: This IPA gets its huge, citrus hop-punch from (surprise) Citra and Legacy hops! A healthy addition of both malted and flaked rye adds a subtle spicy touch.  Less subtle is the fact that we've dry-hopped this batch with twice the normal volume, resulting in an intensely hazy, hoppy variation on a taproom favorite.

beers.name: Kinda Hot In These Rhinos
beers.description: Double Golden Rye New England IPA brewed with Simcoe Hops

beers.name: Pyre
beers.description: If a Rye IPA is what you desire, then good thing you found Pyre. In this rye for a rye world, there's hope in hops. Whether oar not you plan on going down with the sip, brave Ryeking, the waves of rye are worth sailing to.

beers.name: Leo v. Ursus: Inferos
beers.description: Inferos is an imperial rye IPA that is fiery in color and hellacious in hoppiness. Forged with 25 percent rye grain and loaded with more than four pounds of hops per barrel, Inferos is ultimately a big, spicy beer that will keep the soul warm when a chill is in the air.

beers.name: Station
beers.description: IPA brewed with rye and a touch of caramel malt. Hopped intensely and singularly with Simcoe. Brewed to celebrate the fifth anniversary of Station Taproom!

beers.name: Camera Shy
beers.description: This hazy IPA is brewed with a generous helping of rye for a bit more spice in the malt bill. The result is an extremely drinkable, well-balanced IPA.

beers.name: Weathered Scythe – Rye Barrel-Aged Rye IPA
beers.description: Our beloved first-brewed beer rested in barrels. Scythe is a malt-driven ale crafted with NC Rye and hopped with Mosaic aged in Rye Barrels.

beers.name: Throwing Shapes
beers.description: Brewed with heaps of flaked Rye. Hopped in the kettle with the almighty Simcoe. Then aggressively dry hopped with Equinox and Citra

beers.name: Easy Rye-der
beers.description: A full-bodied, unfiltered DIPA brewed with Citra hops in the boil along with a heavy Equinox dry-hop. Riverbend's Seashore Black Rye Malt gives Easy Rye-der a rich backbone that evokes spicy, bready tones and a creamy mouthfeel.

beers.name: Two-Headed Ruthless
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Life's A Trip And Then You Rye
beers.description: Rye IPA w/ Columbus, Citra, and Strata Hops

beers.name: Remedy 42
beers.description: A New England Rye IPA that is the answer to the ultimate question! Featuring Galaxy, Eureka! and Citra, this beer has a very full body with flavors of bright orange citrus and stone fruit and a hint of rye spice in the finish.

beers.name: Audition (Barrel-Aged Ruthless Rye IPA)
beers.description: "The past winter, we siphoned some of our spicy and rugged seasonal IPA into bourbon barrels. Before sealing them for nearly three-month hibernation, we dosed the vessels with whole-cone Comet and East Kent Golding hops - a nod to how traditional IPAs were prepped for sea voyages. The explosive aroma seesaws between tropical fruit and vanilla, an overall sweetness tames the barrels' kick, which holds the remnant spice of rye."

beers.name: DDH Chemical Connection
beers.description: Rye IPA doouble dry hopped with El Dorado, Idaho 7 and Chinook

beers.name: Scythe Rye IPA
beers.description: The day of resurrection is at hand, the blade still sharp. Our longest standing beacon of utility, this Rye India Pale Ale invokes the vital tenets of balance not by muting flavors, but by elevating them. A European crystal malt backbone is lifted by the sweet pop of Riverbend Malt’s Wren Abruzzi Rye. Chinook and Columbus hops provide a grapefruit flavor up-front curtained by the powerful aroma of berry and fresh pineapple, thanks to an exclusively modest Mosaic dry-hopping. Finish your work, wipe your brow, and reap this delicious reward. For who knows when it shall perish.

beers.name: Rye Rye Rocco
beers.description: This hazy IPA 40% flake and malted rye in the mash. Hopped with simcoe, german tettnang and citra throughout. Rich mouthfeel, fruit, subtle spice.

beers.name: Hop Damn!
beers.description: Double Rye India Pale ale brewed in collaboration with the metalcore band Every Time I Die. Description from the bottle: "Where rye thrives is not for the faint of heart. Fierce terrain is home. To experience it's resilience requires exiting a comfort zone. This isn't at all unpleasant. Fast, loud and to the point. Savor it."

beers.name: Kiano's Cut Rye Barrel Aged Rye DIPA
beers.description: We brew a series of three beers in honor of our family of Eastern Black rhino friends at Blank Park Zoo. Kiano's Cut is a Cedar Ridge Rye barrel-aged version of Ayana's Rye Double IPA. Named for the male Kiano, meaning "full of joy", this beer is packed full of citrus-forward hops, layered over the spicy rye malt base. Three months in the barrel works to punch up the rye character, while adding a touch of heat. The resulting beer weighs in at 9.2% ABV, packing a rhino-sized wallop. Despite their rough exterior, our rhino friends have a softer, artistic side as well. The artwork on this bottle is a reproduction of the actual artwork the family painted for us with their prehensile lip! So raise a glass to these magnificent creatures, and Blank Park's tireless efforts to save them from extinction.

beers.name: Scythe Rye IPA (Bulliet Rye Barrel-Aged)
beers.description: The harvest lingers on, the blade still sharp, Weathered and beaten through the seasons of wear, the Scythe has our trust when the field grows high. The beacon of utility, our rye india pale ale invokes the vital tenets of balance not by muting flavors, but by elevating them. A European crystal malt backbone is lifted by the herbal pop of Riverbend Malt's Wrens Abruzzi Rye. "C" hops provide a grapefruit finish curtained by the powerful aroma of blueberry & fresh pineapple, thanks to an exclusive Mosaic dry-hopping. Finish your work, wipe your brow, and reap this delicious reward.

beers.name: Oak Aged Rye IPA
beers.description: 2014 AHA National Conference Commemorative Beer

beers.name: Citra Legacy
beers.description: This American-style Rye IPA delivers its one-two hop punch courtesy of a plentiful dose of Citra and Legacy hops.  Citra, of course, is renowned for its lush, tropical character of passionfruit and citrus, while Legacy supplies a lovely herbal background alongside some grapefruit and blackcurrant. A healthy addition of both malted and flaked rye adds a subtle, spicy touch.

beers.name: Forgotten Astronauts
beers.description: Our San Diego-inspired IPA brewed with rye malt and a blend of Nelson Sauvin and Nectaron hops. Expect stellar notes of pink grapefruit, white grapes, and fresh rye bread.

beers.name: reDANKulous
beers.description: This imperial red IPA simultaneously wallops and caresses your senses with its complex hop profile and slightly sweet malt bill.

beers.name: EPO
beers.description: EPO is a New England Red IPA. This brew is red in color, but with the haziness you expect from an East Coast IPA. The malt backbone provides a touch of caramel-like sweetness and the double dry hopping with Mosaic, Sultana and Ella hops gives this brew a strong citrus, papaya and mango aroma/flavor with a hint of pine.

beers.name: IPA - Tequila Barrel Aged
beers.description: Very small batch, fresh IPA aged only 5 months in Tequila barrels, then heavily dry hopped with mosaic just before bottling. Please enjoy fresh, not intended for cellaring (abv is approximate)

beers.name: Imperial Blood of the Unicorn
beers.description: Imperial Red IPA with Cascade, Mosaic and Chinook hops. We've been brewing Blood of the Unicorn for some time now... so thought it was high time to kick this beer into second gear. Imperial Blood of the Unicorn is a bigger, more bold, more metal, Blood of the Unicorn and whoa. This beer has beautiful expressions of pine, citrus, white flowers, and spicy malt notes from the rye malt.

beers.name: Sequoia
beers.description: Sequoia, a Red IPA inspired by the towering trees out west. Sequoia pours a beautiful red hue with a white foam head. It is aggressively hopped with a unique blend of Columbus, Chinook, Nelson, and Simcoe hops. This beer rouses the senses with a rush of orange citrus, sparkling grapefruit, and piney resin. Following behind these snappy aromas are layers of rich caramel and toffee undertones. Unmistakably balanced, complex, and as refreshing as the rarified air found off the beaten path.

beers.name: Double Satan's Mile
beers.description: Amarillo, Chinook & Mosaic-hopped Double Red India Pale Ale

beers.name: Red Over Red
beers.description: Sweet caramel malts and hops go head to head for control of this imperial Red Ale. The hops bring flavors and aromas of pine, passion fruit, peach, mango and citrus. The malts fall short and leave the sweet caramel as just an afterthought. Welcome to hop heaven.

beers.name: JOSE XTRA
beers.description: DDH with citra columbus & simcoe, notes of citrus pine & tropical fruit, blend of bready malt character and hops

beers.name: Stone Pataskala Red X IPA
beers.description: Pat-ASK-ala? Pata-SKALA? Pa-TASK-a-la? While those in the know favor the third pronunciation, no matter how you say it, this is a unique red IPA. The beer was first brewed in September 2015 to support music and arts education programs in Pataskala, Ohio, where Stone co-founder Greg Koch grew up. People there loved it, so we added the beer to our seasonal lineup. The deep crimson hue is courtesy of a fairly new special German malt variety by BESTMALZ called Red X. Dry-hopped with Mosaic, Cascade and Amarillo hops, this beer is incredibly citrus-forward, rounded out with biscuit and toffee notes. We think you’ll find this red IPA to be quite deliciously satisfying, no matter how you choose to pronounce it.

beers.name: Pilot 11
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Red Viper
beers.description: IPA with Hibiscus and Spanish Cedar AddedCan Release 1/29 -$18Like most of our IPAs this one has a vibrant hop flavor with citrus, mango, and berry... but unlike the rest it has a vibrant color! Hibiscus flowers provide their intense pigmentation along with refreshing cranberry and floral aromatics. Aging on Spanish cedar wood plays a supporting role with zesty grapefruit and sandalwood aromatics dancing behind the SImcoe and Nelson Sauvin hops. A vibrant beer to enlighten those gray days.Show Less

beers.name: Destroyer of Worts
beers.description: Mosaic Red IPA

beers.name: Roundhouse
beers.description: Substantial amounts of late-kettle hop additions and dry-hopping yields a heady blend of fruity aromas of pineapple, peach and citrus. Those aromas continue into a crisply bitter hop presence across the tongue, but the judicious use of toasted and caramel specialty malts prevents the hop intensity from overwhelming the palate.Locally sourced Michigan honey creates a smooth, dry finish that pulls everything together.The India Red Ale style is a variation on the IPA, but with more caramel and toasted malt character and a reddish hue.Roundhouse was first brewed at our original brewery in downtown Kalamazoo in 2009.

beers.name: G'Knight®
beers.description: Our “Velvet M-80” is a hefty, dry hopped double-red ipa with a nose full of aroma, a sticky mouthfeel, a malty middle and unctuous hop flavors. G’Knight sports a surprisingly sensuous finish for a beer of its size (8.7% ABV, 60 IBUs). It’s brewed in tribute to a fellow Colorado craft beer pioneer and Vietnam vet who died fighting a 2002 wild fire outside of our Lyons hometown. For all the details behind this tribute follow this link to www.N3978Y.com . G’Mornin’. G’Day. G’Knight.Show Less

beers.name: Camp Slap Squared
beers.description: Camp Slap Red has a special place in all our hearts, but we had always wondered what a “bigger” version would taste like.. So we present to you Camp Slap Squared! This rendition has a slightly higher ABV and almost twice the amount of hops. It hits you with grapefruit and resinous aromatics and drinks with an increased yet balanced hop bite

beers.name: Sir Agravain
beers.description: Agravain Amber IPA. (Ag-ra-vain) This West Coast Style Amber IPA is brewed with Simcoe, Mosaic, and Centennial hops. Red and color and full of hop flavor.

beers.name: Doublethink IPA
beers.description: Imperial Red IPA aggressively hopped with Chinook, Nugget, Cascade, Perle, Zythos, Summit, El Dorado, Mandarina and Centennial hops.

beers.name: Deuce
beers.description: Our 2nd Anniversary Red IPA hits strong with a one-two punch of heady malt, backed up with serious Galaxy and Citra for tropical notes of peach, mango and papaya.

beers.name: Double Bad Polaroid
beers.description: Orange Citrus, Mild Bitterness, Caramel

beers.name: Heavenly Bodies: Mars
beers.description: This Red IPA was brewed with a tasteful blend of caramel and roasted malts bringing a bready, honey sweetness, pouring a beautiful shaded red hue. Balancing that sweetness with frequent Centennial and Amarillo additions throughout the boil for a classic American IPA bitterness. Dry hopped using the same hop combination, we're getting a little crisp black currant and grapefruit aroma foreshadowing the bitterness in this beer. Flavors of fresh lemon, that classic resinous pine, and a hint of refreshing honeydew melon.

beers.name: Satan's Mile
beers.description: Red India Pale Ale hopped with @indiehops Chinook, our 2019 Amarillo & Mosaic. Fruit punch, a clean sheen of pine and grapefruit. Inspired by the red-light district stretch of road in the South Loop back in the day where all types of vice went down.

beers.name: Talking To Mirrors
beers.description: Our Red IPA brewed with German malted barley and a blend of hops from the Pacific Northwest. Expect bright notes of orange, pineapple, and sticky pine.

beers.name: Went And Took It
beers.description: Both the name and style of this beer are inspired by our Texas Rangers' legendary World Series run, and the beer tastes as delicious as the victory. Brewed with Citra, Mosaic, Simcoe, and Nelson Sauvin hop kief.

beers.name: Lurky
beers.description: Red NE IPA that has a tropical fruit aroma and is juicy with a grapefruit and slight malty taste. This beer is brewed with wheat.

beers.name: Red Giant Finality (Bragging Rights 2019)
beers.description: This collaborative effort with Heinen's Grocery Stores allows a local homebrewer the opportunity to scale up their winning recipe and get their hands dirty with our brewing team. This year’s winner, Doug Wiedemann, made a fantastic Red IPA called Red Giant Finality, that shined above the rest.

beers.name: Ghost Fox
beers.description: With just enough kilned malt to give it color, this beer is in all other ways a traditional west coast, with a nice, dry palate and solid bitterness. Simcoe and Cascade provide beautiful floral, piney, and resinous qualities, with Amarillo bringing the fruit to balance. Prospectors and civilians alike report seeing a huge, red, devilish looking beast carrying a skeleton on its back. A farmer shot the beast in 1893, discovering that it was in fact a large, red camel, with a skeleton attached to its back. While its true origins are unknown, it is believed to be the corpse of a prospector who was dying in the desert and strapped himself to his camel in hopes that it would lead him to water.HOPS: CTZ, Simcoe, Cascade, Amarillo

beers.name: Red Hazy IPA
beers.description: Brewed with Vienna and Munich malts and dry hopped with Citra, Ekuanot, Amarillo, Simco and Mosaic hops. .

beers.name: Killer Red
beers.description: “Fresh Hop Strong IRA” It’s harvest time again, which means using just-picked hops straight from Sodbuster Farm in the Willamette Valley. Our choice of hops for the Killer Green were a little late this year, so we decided to craft a sister brew with fresh Perles to fill the thirsty void. Killer Red has distinct apple/pine/orange notes from the hops, and pulls that biscuit/caramel character you find in our India Red Ale (“IRA”). Drinks like it’s IRA, but the extra strength is worth respecting. 7.3% ABV, 88 BU

beers.name: Cold Blooded Cryo Blood of the Unicorn
beers.description: Cryo Hopped Red Ale

beers.name: Partner Ships #1: Red IPA
beers.description: Red IPA brewed at Heavy Seas Beer in collaboration with Maine Beer Company.

beers.name: Batch 200 Double Red IPA
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: No Prison Can Hold Me
beers.description: Complex layers of pine and resin. caramel malt & toastyhint. Pleasant warmth.Features Citra, Simcoe, Rakau, and Motueka hops.

beers.name: 6252 Red IPA w/Honey
beers.description: 60# of honey from bee hives along the lake Michigan coast provide a very smooth non-bitter finish to this well hopped American Red IPA. Aromatic hop use includes resinate compounds from the Simcoe and Mosaic hop varieties, while Organic Chinooks hops from Midwest farms do the bittering. Then finished with another generous dry hop addition of Mosaic pellet hops.

beers.name: Nightmare On Troutman Street
beers.description: Resin, pine, grapefruit, and quite possibly possessed. Brewed on Halloween night in collaboration with Bitter & Esters Homebrew Shop and the Brewminaries Homebrew Club. Chinook, Galaxy, Citra and Simcoe hops. Hazy red hue. Join the Dank Side...

beers.name: JOSE XTRAVAGANZA
beers.description: brewed with simcoe, cascade, and columbus, full-flavored, piney hop notes

beers.name: Infernal Machine
beers.description: Hoppy Red Ale with Mosaic and Rakau hops.

beers.name: Tyranny Red IPA
beers.description: Tyranny is absolute power vested in a single ruler. This Red India Pale Ale commands all authority, relegated in unflinching decrees of dank, resinous hops and the absolute foundation of crimson and crystal malts. Balanced unlike any ruler before, there is no chink in its hop-fortified armor. Surrender to Tyranny is unconditional.

beers.name: Uncle Bubby
beers.description: Brewed in honor of our beloved brother and friend, Oliver Bailey. His favorite holiday was St. Patrick’s Day and his birthday was the day after. We built this beer as we saw Ollie…A pseudo redhead with hoppy tendencies, strong but approachable and always left you feeling good. Cheers, my friend.

beers.name: Isle of You
beers.description: This is a big, bold IPA brewed with 2-row, medium crystal malts, flaked barley and a touch of black malt for a reddish hue. We hopped it in the kettle and fermenter with Simcoe, Bravo, and Centennial, to give it a fruity, citrusy hop character. It is relatively dry, and inviting for an 8.6% ABV beer.

beers.name: Ruby Falls
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Juicy Red IPA
beers.description: Malty, sweet, and very smooth. A juicy version of Bell’s Roundhouse IRA.

beers.name: Reddy Kilowatt
beers.description: A Red IPA brewed with 5 diferent malts and 3 diferent hop varieties. Bold malt flavor and ruby red color is balanced by punget hop flavors and aromas coming fro Mosaic, Centenial, and Amarillo hops.

beers.name: Stone Pilot Series: Red IPA
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Dual Rotor
beers.description: Wet hopped red IPA brewed with fresh picked MI Chinook and dry hopped with more Chinook & Cascade pellets.

beers.name: Red Wolf Red IPA
beers.description: The world's largest walk-through zoo in the world is located RIGHT HERE in Asheboro, NC. The North Carolina Zoo is seven miles from Four Saints Brewing Company, and this is the FIRST collaborative beer we've brewed with the North Carolina Zoo Society to support their world-leading conservation efforts. American red wolf conservation is just one North Carolina Zoo project highlighted in the new series from Nat Geo WILD, “Secrets of the Zoo: North Carolina.”Our Red Wolf Red IPA is a medium-bodied hoppy beer with a complex yet clean taste profile. 10 percent of the proceeds of all Red Wolf Red IPA sales will benefit American red wolf conservation efforts at the North Carolina Zoo.

beers.name: Razzberry IPA
beers.description: Red IPA steeped on Raspberry Tea

beers.name: Listen To the River
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: 6252 - Simcoe
beers.description: Super smooth, malty rich, red IPA crafted from 7 different malted barley varieties, and spiced heavily with both Simcoe, and Mosaic hops in the kettle. Then hit again with a strong dose of Simcoe post fermentation.

beers.name: Red Whale
beers.description: The 2022 SF Beer Week Collab from the the Bay Area Guild. Crazy hops (Citra/Galaxy/Strata), crazy color, crazy aroma & flavor, not one to miss!

beers.name: Triple Vegan
beers.description: Triple IPA with Citra, Galaxy & Nelson hops.

beers.name: HDHC More Citra Than All Citra
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: HDHC Triple Citra Daydream
beers.description: The biggest and hoppiest gets even bigger and hoppier but with a very smooth profile with the help of our oat cream treatment. Citra, Citra Cryo and Citra incognito turn this beer into a lychee and tropical fruit hop bomb.

beers.name: LAX 2 JFK
beers.description: Collaboration with Other Half Triple IPA with Moteuka, Citra and Simcoe.Show Less

beers.name: Triple Butcher
beers.description: Triple IPA w/ mosaic, Galaxy, Nelson

beers.name: JFK 2 LAX
beers.description: Collaboration Triple IPA w/ Other Half Brewing in NYC, hopped with Motueka, Citra, and Simcoe.

beers.name: Very DDDoublegangerrr
beers.description: Very DDDoubleganger is the ultimate expression of our Alter Ego family of beers. Born out of a desire to continue pushing the envelope, this beer will ignite your senses in every way with epic hop saturation propelled by a dense body and tongue-coating mouthfeel. Pouring a wild hazy orange color into your glass, this beast carries dense notes of tropical fruit, a medley of mango and citrus, and summer stone fruit that is so juicy it's hard to believe it is concocted of just water, malt, hops, and yeast. It finishes cleanly with a palate-coating bitterness that entices your next sip. Rivaled only by the Almighty Julius, this one is truly special-Enjoy!

beers.name: Death Mettle
beers.description: The newest member of our Mettle group is Death Mettle a Triple IPA in a devilishly drinkable disguise. Combining the hop bills of both Mettle and Heavy Mettle, we've created this intensely hop-saturated experience to pair perfectly with the ghosts and goblins of Halloween. Pouring a thick, hazy golden yellow, Death Mettle opens with concentrated aromas of juicy mango, pineapple, orange zest, and mixed stone fruit. Full-bodied, extremely tropical, and plush on the palate, this beer is built to satisfy the most chilling of hop cravings.

beers.name: Dragonsaddle
beers.description: The strong “herbal” aroma sends you back to freshmen year catching a ride to school in your weird burnout neighbor’s ____(insert your fav. El Camino, IROC, Firebird) whilst being bombarded by the sounds of Van Halen (DLR era, none of that Sammy Hagar synthy love song bullshit). DANKSOME! The flavor profile is full-on drippingly ripe tropical fruits: Mango, guava, papaya, and citrus. Juicy, refreshing, and deceptive. We would highly recommend wearing a helmet & supportive cup when mounting the Dragonsaddle.

beers.name: Blowin' Smoke
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Laboratory Waves
beers.description: Laboratory Waves has everything you love in Straight Out Of The Laboratory with a balanced amount of lactose added, creating a beer with an even softer and creamier finish. It pours a hazy and very bright tangerine with aromas of freshly squeezed citrus, lime and grapefruit and a tropical fruit character and an overall aroma that mimics island tiki drinks. The flavor is absolutely tremendous with notes of bright tropical orange juice, mango smoothie, and dank grass. The finish is constantly evolving in your mouth as it goes from an escalating brightness beaming with our signature #EQjuicemorphing into a soft and creamy tropical fruit flavored popsicle with a touch of sweetness. This may be the smoothest TIPA to come out of our lab yet!

beers.name: Platinum Fern
beers.description: Platinum Fern is an amped up, Triple IPA version of Silver Fern that exhibits the splendor of New Zealand hops. As it fills your glass, Nelson and Peacharine Hops meld the sweet perfume of white grape and summery peach. Beneath this harmony, Motueka hops burst with flavors of tropical fruits, while Waimea hops provide a subtle blend of citrus peel and woody aromatics. We hope you enjoy this dangerously drinkable treat and ponder what treasures lie hidden in plain sight.

beers.name: Matthew Matthew Matthew From The Veil Veil Veil
beers.description: DDH Triple IPA w/ Citra and Enigma. TIPA version of Matt Matt from the Veil Veil. Released 5/7/20.

beers.name: All Hundred Thousand Trillion Everything
beers.description: All of the Trillions! Our friends from Other Half came to town for the third iteration of our collab series, and we came out of it with All Hundred Thousand Trillion Everything Triple IPA. Everything Galaxy, everything we love in massively flavorful hoppy beer.AHTTE pours a lusciously hazy shade of orange with tropical aromas of fresh mango, papaya, and kiwi bursting out of the glass. Taste follows with candied peach, cantaloupe, and ruby red grapefruit adding to the melange of fruit. At twice the hopping rate of last years Two Hundred Thousand Trillion Everything, we dropped the fruit addition and ratcheted things up to hefty 9.8% ABV, leaving a pleasant sweetness and soft bitterness to balance the muscle. Completely satisfying but always inviting you back for the next sip.

beers.name: LAX2JFK: In the Clouds
beers.description: This Triple Oat Cream IPA presents a golden yellow color with heavy haze. Waves of fruit salad-like aromas crash over the palate, offering intense notes of mango nectar, orange creamsicle, mixed berry compote, and juicy nectarine. Thanks to a generous addition of oats and a gentle application of milk sugar, the mouthfeel is plush, with a markedly well-hidden alcohol presence and a lightly sweet finish.

beers.name: VitaminM(Sea)³
beers.description: Ocean Physics spans from small millimeter-scale turbulence to big-scale global circulation (like the label) and even applies to fish tanks in your living room. For this beer, we payed attention to smallest detail while thinking of a big TIPA that you can enjoy in your living room and possibly in your fish tank if you have too many. Thanks Ocean Physics. When Dino and Mike visited Middletown a few weeks ago to follow up on the collab we did with Vitamin Sea Brewing at their place, VitaminM(Sea)², we set out to make a triple as smooth as the most gentle ocean waves.VitaminM(Sea)³ starts with a base of oats and wheat to help the beer remain soft and creamy before being aggressively hopped with citra, mosaic, wakatu, and galaxy. It pours a hazy bright straw yellow and has intense notes and flavors of assorted citrus, lemon & lime, and a dank and earthy lemongrass. It has big #EQjuice with an extremely soft smooth finish. It’s dangerously drinkable for a triple and will slip you into meditative state as you are reminded of the sounds of the sea as the ocean boost your brain power… or helps you drink in a fish tank.

beers.name: The Big One
beers.description: The Big One is our first canned triple IPA. It is brewed and dry-hopped with a tremendous amount of hops roughly approximating the Haze hop bill. It tastes like orange juice, tropical fruit, and mango with a robust and supple mouthfeel. We brewed it for you--Enjoy!

beers.name: The Solution
beers.description: The Solution is a Triple IPA brewed with a proprietary yeast blend and meticulously crafted construct that combines over a decade of hoppy beer refinement.It utilizes an enormous hop charge of Peacharine alongside accent hops that we have traveled the world to source. Pouring a glowing yellow color into your glass, it tastes like super ripe tropical fruit, mixed citrus, and peach nectar with a pleasing and quenching bitterness. Most importantly, it tastes as good at the end of the glass as it does at the beginning of it.We hope you enjoy it as much as we do.

beers.name: Conjoined Triangles of Success
beers.description: We concocted this beer with our friends at HBO to celebrate the season and series finale of Silicon Valley. We're hoping for more daily active users than a click farm which is why this offering contains hops like Citra, Citra Cryo, Citra Incognito, Cashmere, Galaxy, and Motueka.

beers.name: Every Trillion Ever
beers.description: The fourth iteration of our collaborative series with our good friends at Other Half Brewing, Every Trillion Ever is an all Mosaic Triple IPA set upon a simple base of Two Row and Flaked Oats. Pouring a light orange color with eye catching haze, Every Trillion Ever offers bursting tropical aromas of ripe mango, sweet pineapple and vibrant citrus peel that leap right out of the glass. The palate follows with luscious notes of passion fruit, juicy tangerine, and mixed berry sorbet adding to the boundless layers of flavors. Medium bodied with a pillowy soft mouthfeel, Every Trillion Ever has a pleasant sweetness that coincides with a lovely floral bite making for a smooth and enjoyable finish.

beers.name: Sexier Fluctuation
beers.description: Sexier Fluctuation takes our Citra/Galaxy blend found in Sexual Fluctuation and supersizes it into an even juicier Triple IPA. It pours a hazy tangerine orange releasing intense aromas of passion fruit, peach, lime, and pineapple while using our latest and greatest processes to pull out as much #EQjuice as possible. The taste is fruity and velvety like a tropical creamsicle. Like all of our TIPA’s, we find this beer dangerously smooth and super drinkable.

beers.name: Triple Lustra
beers.description: Going just one more step beyond, Lustra get's it's final boost into the Triple category. Big body and immense hop saturation, without being overly bitter or boozy. This is the biggest beer we've ever done, with the most hops we've ever hopped.

beers.name: 4th Anniversary Is A Zombie
beers.description: It just won't die. And for good reason as this has been one of our favorite Triple IPAs of all time. Brewed with Pilsner malt, oats and wheat before being aggressively hopped with Citra, Galaxy, Enigma, El Dorado, Mosaic and Citra Cryo and double dry hopped with the same. Then, we gave it two more dry hop additions of Galaxy, Citra Cryo and Mosaic. Soft and juicy.⁠⁠Artwork by @dayolddonuts

beers.name: Climb The Ballmer Peak (Batch 2)
beers.description: Using the biggest dose yet of our 2020 hand selected Citra, Climb The Ballmer Peak Batch 2 is here.The Ballmer Peak - Steve Ballmer of Microsoft discovered a correlation between cognitive ability, creativity, problem solving, and performance after you indulge in an alcohol beverage. This sweet spot is known as the Ballmer Peak. When we had the pleasure of having JC from Trillium here, we talked about how much we loved the Ballmer Peak collaboration we brewed in Canton in back in 2019 (possibly mid-peak). Keeping the recipe similar, we wanted to revisit the beer that helped form precious moments, enhanced BBQ recipes, friendships, and of course delicious recipes. To help you obtain this experience, we will help you Climb the Ballmer Peak.Climb The Ballmer Peak uses our Super fractal base and fermentation and is hopped exclusively with hand selected Citra. This TIPA pours an opaque bright orange and has an intense juice forward aroma of Mango, Passionfruit, Pineapple, and Rainbow Melon. We don’t know exactly what rainbow melon is, but we want to stay true to our emotional responses that occur while we Climb the Ballmer peak. Flavors and bright notes of deep navel orange, drippy peach, passionfruit, grapefruit and lime go along with a touch of berry and lychee in a juicy and thick mouthfeel. The EQ juice profile is extreme, and this beer can easily pass as a juice drink, although reaching your Ballmer Peak after just a few sips may say otherwise.

beers.name: Dialed-Up: Chardonnay & Gewürztraminer
beers.description: Dialed-Up builds upon the foundation of our series of Double IPA’s brewed with grape must, Dialed In. For this special release, we bumped the ABV all the way up to 11% and massively dry hopped the beer with Galaxy and Citra. Pouring a gorgeous maize yellow with a heavy, milky haze, Dialed Up offers an intense nose layering ample aromas of orange smoothies, overripe melons and sweet table grapes with dank, blooming pine. A bold wave of pulpy citrus leads on the palate with flavors of fresh squeezed pomelo, grapefruit, and blood orange. Next, the mid-fermentation addition of Chardonnay and Gewürztraminer juices converge with vinous notes of lychee, apricot, passion fruit, orange blossom honey, sweet pineapple, and roses. With a soft and creamy mouthfeel and medium-to-full body, Dialed-Up’s finish balances its sweeter tropical notes with a moderate and enjoyable floral bitterness.

beers.name: Ballmer Peak
beers.description: Legend tells of a mythical "peak" that the human brain can hit after a beer or two - atop this peak all tasks flow with creativity and ease. Computer programs come to life, musical symphonies are born... and delicious beer recipes are created. We worked with the scientific geniuses from Equilibrium Brewery on an all Citra-hopped triple IPA that represents the precarious wonder of this Ballmer Peak. Pouring an eye catching golden yellow with a heavy milky haze, Ballmer Peak has an explosively aromatic nose revealing mouthwatering tones of mango nectar, pineapple slices, and vibrant orange peel. Ripe stone fruit flavors of apricot and peach build on the palate adding to a melange of tropical papaya, lime, melon and lychee. With a pillowy soft mouthfeel, pleasant biscuity sweetness, and rounded floral bitterness, Ballmer Peak is an open invitation to explore your own creativity.

beers.name: Biggest One
beers.description: The Biggest One is a triple IPA brewed and dry-hopped with a preposterous amount of hops. It tastes like the nectar of freshly pressed oranges, mixed tropical fruit, and juicy summer stone fruit with a massive and coating mouthfeel. It's a Tree House hoppy beer gluttony in the best way possible. Enjoy!

beers.name: WeDedMon³
beers.description: We overloaded this beer with Citra for an intense, layered, and delicious tropical experience. We gave it an extra week to condition just to round things out even more

beers.name: Blowin’ Up the Spot
beers.description: Our collaboration with our friends at Monkish Brewing. Blowin’ Up the Spot Imperial IPA is our sequel to JFK 2 LAX, our collab brewed at Monkish. It clocks in at 10.2% and is hopped with Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, El Dorado and large amounts of Citra and Mosaic lupulin powders.

beers.name: The Resolution
beers.description: The Riddle but with liquid hop products. The Resolution is a Triple IPA brewed with a proprietary yeast blend and meticulously crafted construct that combines over a decade of hoppy beer refinement.It utilizes an enormous hop charge of hand-selected hops and proprietary liquid hop extracts that we have traveled the world to source. Pouring a glowing yellow color into your glass, it tastes like super ripe tropical fruit, mixed citrus, and peach nectar with a pleasing and quenching bitterness.

beers.name: Straight Outta The Laboratory
beers.description: We love science and we have been feverishly working in the lab to bring you our most recent achievements. We started with the Straight Outta Middletown grain bill, supersized the citra portion, applied our latest and greatest technology (think of the EQ juice in raining belma and last batch of MC²) and ended up with January Fluctuation on steroids with the most amount of EQ juice to date.Straight Outta The Laboratory pours a hazy bright tangerine and has aromas of freshly squeezed citrus, lime, grapefruit, and a tropical character that makes actual tropical fruit green with envy. The flavor is explosive with notes of bright tropical orange juice, mango smoothie, and dank grass. It’s resinous and chewy with an escalating brightness and a just a touch of residual sweetness balanced by a soft bitterness. We are particularly proud of this beer as it’s the culmination of months and months of hard work (since January Fluctuation).

beers.name: Dream Wave Distortion
beers.description: We took Dream Wave Fluctuation, our collab with our friends from Brooklyn and blurred the lines to explore what it would would be like with a life as a TIPA. This aggressively hopped galaxy and citra forward triple uses oats and lactose to match Other Half's Dream treatment and creates a scaled up and dangerously drinkable version of its predecessor.Dream Wave Distortion pours a hazy tangerine color. It has big aromas of passion fruit, melon, peach, cream, and pineapple with a matching flavor profile. Utilizing some of our latest techniques, this triple is lethally smooth with a bright, luscious, and creamy sorbet #EQjuice finish.

beers.name: Lupus Salictarius
beers.description: It was great having Mortalis Brewing come to hang a few weeks ago. We all decided to pay homage to the Hops we use on a daily basis. Lupus Salictarius, which literally translates as “wolf of the willows”, is disputably the first hop plants and is said to be the botanical name immortalized by a famous Roman Philosopher (who is also an extremely tasty West Coast IPA. Respect). Tying into the Latin references Mortalis uses, we decided on a recipe that showcases some of our new favorite hops to pay homage to the OG of hops and Lupus Salictarius was born.We started off with a base of 2 row, flaked oats and white wheat before adding a giant addition of Citra and Idaho7 in the whirlpool. We dry hopped with some of our favorites; Citra, Nelson, and Galaxy to finish it of with a big bang. This triple is an absolute explosion of tropical dankness. Big guava, sweet tangerine citrus, white grape, and a touch of passionfruit. It has a smooth but prominent chewy mouthfeel and has big notes of our signature EQJuice that really showcases what these hops have to offer.

beers.name: More lACEd In Space
beers.description: All Citra Everything and Space Diamonds smashed together into one big, hop forward Citra and Galaxy triple IPA.

beers.name: Wetsuit
beers.description: Summer is back and it’s time to dive into another project with our friends from Evil Twin! Building on the base recipe of our previous beach inspired collaborations, Trillikini and Board Shorts, we’ve once again bumped up the malt bill and increased the dry hop of Amarillo, Citra and Mosaic to create this Triple IPA. With an appearance of vivid yellow straw, Wetsuit offers an engaging nose of Meyer lemon, orange pith, and overripe pineapple. The palate bursts with tropical flavors of juicy mango, sweet clementines, creamy honeydew melon, ripe stonefruit, and subtle vanilla. A soft, fluffy mouthfeel provides a full body and a smooth finish with a balanced bite.

beers.name: Science & Sorcery
beers.description: It’s a pleasure to release our first collab with Justen from Electric Brewing Company, someone we have become fast friends with after having so much in common.Science & Sorcery takes elements, themes, and processes from both breweries and melds them into one magical potion.We start off with a giant base off of oats and wheat and a massive dose of Citra and Galaxy for the hop bill (Think close to Space Dream Lab rates).Science & Sorcery pours an ELECTRIC yellow with aromas and flavors of tropical passionfruit, papaya, pineapple, melon, and key lime. Soft and crushable, this beer is straight juice with a velvety and creamy mouthfeel and an extreme #EQjuice finish that will have you seeing apparitions and wondering… is there actually a difference between science and sorcery?

beers.name: HDHC Triple Citra Daydream
beers.description: This is the hoppiest beer out of Equilibrium. EVER. Using a big base of wheats and oats, we used an all Citra combo of our hand selected Citra, Citra Incognito, and Citra LUPOMAX to make out biggest dry-hopped beer to date. To meet Daydream criteria, we finished with a touch of lactose.HDHC Triple Citra Daydream pours opaque and vivid yellow and has very strong aromas of futuristic mango supported by a tropical character that makes actual tropical fruit a hoppy green with envy. The flavor is explosive with notes of mango smoothie, orange juice, touch of dank grass, and #rainbowmelon. It’s resinous and chewy with an Other Half’s aggressive hoppy character that’s balanced with our #EQjuice that will have you daydreaming after each sip.

beers.name: HDHC Triple Broccoli Special Reserve
beers.description: One of our favorite triple IPAs so far in 2020 gets the High Density Hop Charge treatment. Mountains of Citra, Mosaic, Simcoe and Hallertau Blanc T-90 hop pellets get mixed with Citra, Mosaic, and Simcoe Cryo pellets and the whole thing is awash in Citra and Mosaic Incognito.

beers.name: The Riddle
beers.description: The Riddle is a Triple IPA brewed with a proprietary yeast blend and meticulously crafted construct that combines over a decade of hoppy beer refinement. It utilizes an enormous hop charge of hand-selected hops that we have traveled the world to source. Pouring a glowing yellow color into your glass, it tastes like super ripe tropical fruit, mixed citrus, and peach nectar with a pleasing and quenching bitterness. We hope you enjoy it as much as we do.

beers.name: Triple Mosaic Dream High-Density Hop Charge
beers.description: Imperial IPA(10.5%) Triple Mosaic Dream gets the high density hop charge treatment with our hand picked T-90 Mosaic pellets, Mosaic cryo and a new special Mosaic hop product for some extra Mosaic goodness. All the flavor and pop of a 15 lb/bbl hop charge but way smoother.

beers.name: Daily Personal Best
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Einstein's Delight
beers.description: Einstein’s Delight is a play off one of his favorite desserts, Orange Sticky Cake, which we first debuted on Energy Evolution Day as Einstein’s Favorite. We wanted to explore the possibilities and swapped out vanilla with a creamy marshmallow twist.We took our SOTL base, added some of our favorite hops and a galactic dose of Florida navel orange zest and Marshmallow. This dessert themed beer has bright notes and flavors of tropical orange slices and assorted citrus and sweet creamy marshmallow frosting. This beer is fun and tasty. It’s extremely smooth and reminds us of an orange creamsicle dipped in a jar of Fluff. A delight Einstein would love.No lactose was harmed while making this beer..

beers.name: Even More Unbalanced
beers.description: This is the hoppiest beer ever brewed at Equilibrium to date. We were discussing with Jeppe how we consider Fluctuation to be perfectly unbalanced and he suggested that we push things even further. We decided to brew Even More Unbalanced together using a blend of Citra, Galaxy, Denali, Mosaic, and Amarillo with boundary pushing hop totals. It pours an intensely hazy glowing tangerine color releasing a penetrating hop blast of bright tropical mango, pineapple, apricot, and berry. The taste is blended tropical fruit that showcases the EQ juice experiments to date while remaining fluffy but with a proper bitterness for balance. If we would do anything over with this batch it would only be to change its name to: Give me your car keys. Please drink this responsibility, it’s a touch dangerous and can sneak up on you quickly.

beers.name: Socratic Questioning 50
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: ImdonewithU!
beers.description: ImdonewithU is the next installment in our 0 IBU series. This time we bumped it up to an 11% Triple IPA version. 0 IBUs and hopped 50/50 with Citra and Mosaic like IdontwanttoBU and IdonteverwanttoBU.

beers.name: Super Fractal Phoenix Set
beers.description: The Phoenix set consists of values such that an arbitrarily small change can cause drastic changes in the sequence of iterated function values (duh) resulting in beautiful shapes and lots of spirals. Keeping with our fractal tradition, we started off with a super simple grain bill of 2row and our specific fractal fermentation profile. We used a big Citra and Idaho 7 whirlpool with some of our favorite hops in the dry hop: Citra, Sabro, Strata, and Galaxy.Super Fractal Phoenix Set pours an opaque yellow tangerine and has a big citrus nose. The flavors are a unique blend of tropical fruits, citrus, “our melon thing”, passionfruit, and an underlying dankness. This beer is extremely aromatic, crushable and smooth with an EXTREME #EQjuice profile that might just leave you seeing beautiful shapes and spirals.

beers.name: Triple Sunshine
beers.description: The culmination of our Sunshine series is exploding with juicy notes of pineapple, grapefruit and lychee. Triple Sunshine exudes potent floral and herbal aromas from a deluge of dry-hopping.

beers.name: Monkish 7: TIPA W/ Cream
beers.description: Anniversary Triple IPA made with Milk Sugar and Citra, Galaxy, Simcoe, Mosaic, and Idaho 7.

beers.name: 8th Anniversary Collaborative Imperial IPA
beers.description: Brewed with our friends at Fidens, Equilibrium, and Vitamin Sea. For our 8th Anniversary, we brought together some of our favorite NE IPA brewers to cook up a big triple IPA crammed with Citra, Citra Cryo, Citra Incognito, and some accent Idaho 7 and Cascade. The Idaho 7 is hotside only and brings forth a candied pineapple character while the Citra and Cascade are in the dry hop bringing a big orange citrus and lychee character.

beers.name: Apocalipsis
beers.description: 2x mash (meaning twice the normal amount of grain), quadruple dry hopped, quadruple hazy india pale ale featuring all of our favorite hops/hop products from our Cuatro Jinetes series. Simcoe 702, Simcoe Cryo, Mosaic Lupomax, Citra, Citra Cryo, Nelson and Nelson Hop Kief.

beers.name: MURK MERCHANTS (RETIRED)
beers.description: Damn. 500 Batches. A Quadruple IPA only seemed right. We’ve spent the last 3 ½ years getting to know ingredients, processes and our brewhouse in pursuit of cramming as much hop flavor, aroma & oil into these exercises in excess as possible. Citra, Strata, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, Simcoe Cryo, Cashmere Cryo, HBC 692 & Australian Galaxy in every nook & cranny. We love these beers, we love trying to make them better & we love that you’re taking this journey with us. Here’s to the next 500. Pour Up.

beers.name: NPBC7 QDH Hazy QIPA
beers.description: NPBC7 Quadruple Dry Hopped Hazy Quintuple India Pale Ale. Our little brewery only turns 7 once so we decided to have a little fun and brew up our first (and probably only haha) 15% ABV beer! This beautiful, easy drinking masterpiece is bursting with tons of orange sherbert on the nose that lead the way to a tasting experience of fruit punch, tropical pineapple, juicy mango, red strawberry and white peach notes. We are excited to push the boundaries of beer and even more excited to share it with you all!

beers.name: The Spell of the Sorcerer's Skull
beers.description: The Brujos Brewing overlord paid us a visit, and we made something truly magical together. The Spell of the Sorcerers Skull TDH Hazy QIPA is 12% and loaded with Citra, Galaxy, and Rakau hops, conjuring up notes of juicy peach, ripe apricot, and passion fruit.

beers.name: Plane Over Car Over Train Over Boat
beers.description: Boston is known for its complex tangled transportation web. Unbeknownst to many, though, we also have a rarity that exists in only three locations in the world. At a short span on the Charles River is a place where a plane can fly over a train that rides over a car that drives over a boat. Inspired by this representation of the vibrancy of our city, we created the most amplified hoppy beer to hit our tanks. Plane over Train over Car over Boat reflects the seamless, stunning poetry of many synchronized parts moving together in a small space to create a greater whole. A beer that took a year of focused development and tweaking and fine-tuning to bring to life.PoCoToB is our first ever Quadruple IPA. With a bumped up grain bill, we dosed this beer with massive additions of Citra, Mosaic, and Galaxy at our highest hopping rate to date. Pouring a heavily hazy orange color, the nose instantly is greeted with bold aromas of of creamy mango purée, candied lemon, tropical papaya, and underripe pineapple. PoCoToB’s luscious, full mouthfeel accentuates dynamic flavors of juicy apricot, sticky cantaloupe, and pulpy orange smoothies with a touch of guava. PoCoToB has a present yet smooth bite of spruce tips with mouthwatering and clean finish. An extended cold-conditioning period mellows the hoppy bite that often highlights beers of this magnitude, while also further developing the depth of tropical and citrus-like qualities that the intense dry hopping imparted.

beers.name: Fourth Anniversary Ale
beers.description: Fourth Anniversary Ale is a Quadruple Dry Hopped Quadruple IPA

beers.name: When I Was 12
beers.description: Quad IPA with Motueka, Simcoe and Citra hops.

beers.name: When I Was 12 Again
beers.description: Double Dry Hopped (DDH) Quadruple IPA super hop saturated with Citra, Rakau, and Simcoe.

beers.name: NNNN
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Squandering Citra
beers.description: At the far end of the brewery where Mr. Hop-Fu! stands, he watches over the Citra, bag after bag. What to do with it all? Then he first saw the cans, and a recipe, he began to call. With great skillful skill and great speedy speed, the brew team went dry-hopping, quadruple times indeed. There’s only one thing this brew could turn out to be: Squandering Citra, a Fine-Something-That-All-People-Need, of the Hazy QIPA variety! As for the flavor…describe it? That’s hard, we don’t know if we can. It’s grapefruity, zesty, with a touch of lychee. Lemony, watermelony, and even a bit peachy. Grab your Citra-loving friend, tell them to come on! Snag a 4-pack while we have it, and before it’s all gone.

beers.name: Nuclear Option
beers.description: Northeast QIPA. DDH With Citra, Citra And More Citra.Exploding With White Peach, Pineapples, Snake Fruit And Cotton Candy.

beers.name: Axle
beers.description: (TDH) QUADRUPLE IPA super hop saturated with Citra, Galaxy, and Motueka.

beers.name: Personal Submarine
beers.description: The 4th annual nautical inspired collaboration with our friends from EvilTwin Brewing, Personal Submarine is our second ever Quad IPA, building upon the recipe from previous years with an amplified malt bill and one of our heaviest hop charges to date with Amarillo, Citra, and Mosaic. Cracking the can, Personal Submarine is explosively tropical and citrus forward on the nose filling the glass with a gorgeous, eye catching haze of vibrant orange. On the palate, huge flavors of sweet mango, diced pineapple, and ripe papaya take the lead graced by waves of freshly squeezed orange juice, bright lemon and stone fruit. These flavors coalesce towards the finish calling to mind a luscious tropical smoothie highlighted by a soft, fluffy mouthfeel and full body with a smooth grassy bitterness that cuts the sweeter notes.

beers.name: NPBC6 TDH Hazy QIPA
beers.description: To celebrate our 6th anniversary, we created an absolutely face-melting Triple Dry-Hopped Hazy QIPA. This monstrous 13% beer was crafted with pilsner malt and oats for a delightfully thick mouthfeel, before being jam-packed full of Citra, Nelson, Citra Cryo, Peacharine, and Galaxy hops. It sports notes of juicy mango, pineapple, peach, fruit cocktail, and we think it’s nothing short of stellar.

beers.name: The Dank Vault
beers.description: We all know hops are worth their weight in gold in Parkburg, and no expense was spared in creating The Dank Vault! Scrooge McHop and grand-nephews Tyson, John and Zach cracked the cold-safe and dove into their hop reserves in search of the perfect combination for “The Hoppiest Hazy in the World”. Citra, Citra Cryo, Citra 702, Simcoe, Simcoe Cryo, Nectaron Cryo and Nelson Sauvin add up to an abundance of peach and strawberry aromas, with a hint of cherry thrown in the mix. Stacks of red berry, pink starburst, and bright kiwi notes round out this supremely delicious concoction to create a QDH Hazy Quad IPA that’s straight money.

beers.name: Snake Park
beers.description: For our first Quadruple IPA, we teamed up with our good friends at District 96 Beer Factory for their first official Cali collab to bring you "Snake Park". This TDH Hazy QIPA was conceptualized on our trip out to New York back in November. John and Lorenzo welcomed us with open arms and delivered some crazy exceptional hospitality so we knew we had to brew up something big, hazy and special with those guys!
