A lethal dose of Citra Cryo, Citra Incognito, Nelson and Rakau attack the senses by delivering a deadly strike of tropical pineapple, red strawberry, juicy orange and drippy mango tasting notes. All of us here at North Park Beer Company strongly encourage you to ENJOY THE SNAKE because we love this beer and think you will too!

beers.name: Forest of Giants
beers.description: Rising from the tanks once again is Forest of Giants, our big and bold murky quadruple IPA. The second batch of this colossal brew is rooted with Citra, Nelson, Riwaka, and Wai-iti hops that intertwine to produce abundant notes of papaya, sugar-apple, and subtle dank. Expect a medium body and a bewilderingly smooth and juicy mouthfeel from this 13% beast.

beers.name: Anytime You Are Anywhere Always
beers.description: Conformity became the world around us. Compromise the lure. And we were all in too deep. Before something changed. The one, and only, amalgamation of our two worlds. The truth is in the Dream Resin. Quadrupel dry-hopped with Citra, Citra Cryo, Nectaron and Galaxy.

beers.name: Reign of Carnage Part 1
beers.description: TDH QUAD collab with North Park. Whirlpooled with Nelson & Galaxy and TDH with Citra, Citra Cryo, & Rakau.

beers.name: PLEAD THE FIFTH
beers.description: You may have noticed we never released an anniversary beer this year. We decided to create a veritable juice tapestry with a large but carefully selected group of some of our favorites to make up for it: Our selected Strata, Citra, Mosaic Cryo, Cashmere, El Dorado Cryo, Strata CGX, German Grungiest, Australian Galaxy, Crosby Estate Comet, Hop Head Farms Chinook from Michigan, Freestyle Farms Nelson Sauvin & Motueka from New Zealand. Stop snitching.

beers.name: Left Brain Dead
beers.description: Hazy Quadruple IPA hopped with Strata, Simcoe, Comet and Amarillo. Collaboration with New Anthem Beer Project in Wilmington, NC.

beers.name: Shadow of the Moon
beers.description: For our 5th anniversary, we wanted to challenge ourselves as a craft brewery and push the limits of our fermentation skills. Coming in at 15% ABV, this murky quintuple IPA is the strongest beer we have ever brewed at Pure Project. Featuring our five favorite hops--Nelson Sauvin (Freestyle Hops, NZ), Strata (Indie Hops, OR), Mosaic (Loftus Ranches, WA), Citra (Wyckoff Farms, WA), and Cashmere (Gooding Farms, ID)--Shadow of the Moon is a true celebration of hops and the farmers who grew them. At 8 pounds of hops per barrel, this is easily the most heavily dry-hopped beer we have made. The result? A subtly warming and stunningly smooth brew bursting with notes of ripe pineapple, honeydew, and a whole lot of dank. Cheers to five years!

beers.name: Seventh Heaven
beers.description: 7th Anniversary Exclusive - Seventh Heaven is only the 2nd Quadruple IPA we've have made, with over 10lbs per barrel of Galaxy, Vic Secret and Citra

beers.name: The Pursued
beers.description: Big and juicy with strong notes of peach with hints of mango and pineapple. Sticky hops remain throughout the finish.

beers.name: Too Stimulated
beers.description: Eric and I went to my local hair salon to discuses our packages. Eric and Scott wanted to make the package 6..2% and Rob, Justin And Myself Said bigger is better. So after we got our dead ends cut off and base color finished we finally came to a decision. We decided to take his stimulus package 4.4% and our stimulus package 8.0%, combined them and brew what the ppl want a 12.4% Sessionsble Quad Ipa.So we used our new technique Binary Arid Hopped not once but twice with Mosaic, El Dorado and Citra , Stunning notes of Sumo Orange, Kumquat, Watermelon, Passion Fruit and our signature D96 Snake fruit finish.

beers.name: JURASSIC WORLD
beers.description: Our buds from Toppling Goliath came back up to up the ante on our previous prehistoric brews. Paying homage to their dino classics & the not infrequent jokes we get about the amount of plants in our taproom, we used earth rattling quantities of our hand-selected Citra & Citra Cryo with Riwaka & Nelson Sauvin. A whole new universe of oil. Tread lightly.

beers.name: His Airness
beers.description: His Airness is a new 12% Quadruple IPA based off our new series of basketball inspired beers. This is the first Quadruple IPA we’ve ever brewed and are exited to share it with you. It’s hopped to the absolute rim with Citra, Citra Cryo, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, Nelson and Galaxy.

beers.name: FOREGONE CONCLUSION
beers.description: Another over the top exhibition of our hedonistic tendencies to celebrate 4 years of questionable financial decisions. Still trying to find out how deep the rabbit hole goes with our hand selected Citra, Strata, Cashmere, HBC 586, Ekuanot Cryo, Galaxy & Riwaka. Finding evermore nooks & crannies to tuck more oil into. How much further can we take this? Let’s find out.

beers.name: Mega-Fu!
beers.description: Triple Dry Hopped Hazy Quadruple India Pale Ale hopped with Citra, Citra Cryo, Citra Incognito, Nelson, Nelson CGX and Galaxy.

beers.name: Pistons
beers.description: Triple Dry Hopped (TDH) Quadruple IPA super hop saturated with Citra, Galaxy, Nelson Sauvin, and Motueka.

beers.name: Cruel Sea
beers.description: Murky Quadruple IPA with Nelson, Citra Cryo & Cashmere Hops

beers.name: Mountains Are Calling
beers.description: Mountains are Calling makes its long-awaited return as we continue our journey to the summit of hop exploration. This murky quadruple IPA is crowned with tropical-dominant Nelson Sauvin, Strata, Mosaic, and Cashmere hops, all packed on top of a soft, medium-full body. Notes of ripe melon, pineapple, and key lime pie roam on the nose, and ascend to flavors of mango sticky rice, mandarin orange and dank on the palate. When the mountains are calling, you must go!

beers.name: Gigantophis
beers.description: We brought back this older technique called Triple Dry Hoping for this one. With our new ESIP. Strata, Cashmere, and Galaxy. Notes of Mango Sorbet, Passion Fruit, Creamy Orange Soaked Phyllo Cake with our signature Snake Fruit Finish

beers.name: Nuclear Queen
beers.description: The missile silos opened. The countdown began. The payloads crammed full of Citra hops deployed to shoot juicy Hellfire directly into this quadruple IPA. With the help of neighboring ally, @district96beer , the Queen rained forth an awesome explosive blast of ripe orangey pineapple fallout. Queen Citra has used the Nuclear Option.

beers.name: THE REAL WORLD: CITRA
beers.description: This is what happens when every form of Citra we could get our hands on stops pulling punches... & starts getting real. Our hand selected Citra, Citra Cryo, Citralicious Hopburst & Citra hop oil in aggressively overcrowded proportions. Find something out about yourself by getting lost in this sauce.

beers.name: The Spell of the Sorcerer's Skull: Part 2
beers.description: The Brujos overlord has returned to help us brew up an encore to a legendary collab. Together we proudly introduce The Spell of the Sorcerer’s Skull: Part 2. This TDH Hazy Quadruple IPA isn’t for the faint of heart: 12% ABV, and loaded with Citra, Krush, Manilita, and Nelson Sauvin. Take a whiff and you’ll be hit with an overwhelming bouquet of tropical notes - passion fruit, mango, and guava galore. Let your tastebuds become entranced with bright citrus, lemongrass, mixed berries, and fresh stonefruit. Proceed with caution, this is a captivating one!

beers.name: Nuclear Power Plant
beers.description: Extra dry-hopped with Simcoe, Mosaic, Nelson, Citra & Amarillo.
Celebrate the 1000th beer brewed at the Answer with the highest ABV IPA we've ever made. 13% Quadruple Hazy IPA dry hopped with Riwaka, Waimea, Nelson, Mosaic, and Cryo Simcoe hops!!!!

beers.name: Serpentine
beers.description: NE Quad IPA

beers.name: Queen of the Yachts
beers.description: Extremely heavily Oated and Spelted North East Style Quadruple India Pale Ale mash hopped with Cascade and Columbus then dry hoopped repeatedly with Luplin Citra, Luplin Mosaic and Nelson Sauvin. Brewed in collaboration with our freinds from Tin Barn Brewing.

beers.name: Verified
beers.description: Verified is a 12% Quadruple IPA. This beer is super smooth and leaves no indication of the ABV. This beer was hopped to the absolute max with Citra, Mosaic, El Dorado, Motueka and Sabro. You don’t need to be an influencer to enjoy this one.

beers.name: Leap Beer
beers.description: Quadruple IPA brewed for the magical 29th day of February that only comes during a Leap Year. Dry hopped heavily with Citra and Nelson.

beers.name: Powerful Beyond Measure
beers.description: Powerful Beyond Measure is a quad IPA that pushes the limits of hop expression with a tropical assortment of Strata, Motueka, Mosaic, and Cashmere hops. Cloudy golden in appearance, it is a bold brew that bursts with flavors of sweet orange, mango and papaya. But beware, this powerful quad is deceptively smooth for its lofty ABV.

beers.name: Quadruple Dobis
beers.description: It is an all out assault of Citra hops on your DOME. Over pounds per barrel of Citra in the dry hop alone! We used three different lots of Citra T90 pellets from 2019 and 2020 crop years as well as our new 2020 Citra Cryo from @yakimachief resulting in layers and layers of mandarin orange, P0G and tangy Girl Scout Cookies, and we ain't talking Thin Mints if ya know what we mean...

beers.name: Cuffing Season
beers.description: Triple dry hopped with Citra, Galaxy and Strata. Notes of orange creamsicle and papaya.

beers.name: DISINTEGRATION
beers.description: You won't need much helping smearing your lipstick after this one. We decided to make a tribute to the greatest break up album of all time for those of us that aren't feeling the warm & fuzzies this time of year. Our hand-selected Strata surrounded by a supportive group of our selected Citra Cryo, Sabro Cryo, Mosaic Cryo, Amarillo Cryo, Cashmere Cryo, Idaho 7 Cryo & Ekuanot Cryo. Boys may not cry, but they certainly do Cryo. Get lost in this one.

beers.name: 96th Amendment
beers.description: We Triple Dry Hopped This Beer and Added Max Amount of SNAKEFRUIT To Create This Monster QIPA

beers.name: 128 Pack
beers.description: Extremely Heavily Wheated and Oated North East style Quadruple India Pale Ale hopped with Amarillo, Columbus, and Incognito El Dorado and then dry hopped repeatedly with Lupulin Mosaic, Lupulin Amarillo, Lupulin Azacca, HBC 630, and Nectaron.

beers.name: Resurrection By Tickle
beers.description: In the beginning, there was Tickle. Through the power of passion and love, one became two. Tiny Tickle was born. Then, what seemed to be a final Trilogy evolved through Death By Tickle into a Quadrilogy of hedonistic excess and the advent of Extra Tickle. What once represented the finality of mortal life has come full circle to life anew. A fifth state of existence has been revealed, forming a Quintet. Resurrection By Tickle, a Quadruple IPA, emerges powerful and pungent, with a pronounced mango and pineapple bouquet brought forth from unimaginable amounts of Cryo-Hops Citra, Mosaic, and Simcoe, and balanced by the candy-like persuasion of El Dorado. To drink from this cup is to drink straight from source-energy itself.

beers.name: Mosaic Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: This variant on Fort Point features Mosaic in the dry hop. Pouring a cloudy, canary gold, Mosaic Fort Port emits a distinctively dank nose of pulpy, fresh squeezed orange, pungent passionfruit, ripe mango and papaya. These notes are further developed on the palate alongside a juicy profile of mandarin flesh and pomelo pith with a touch of spring pine sap for a light bite. Mosaic Fort Point delivers that familiar biscuity, medium body our signature pale ale.

beers.name: Barrel-Aged What Is Enlightenment?
beers.description: Originally brewed to celebrate our second anniversary, What is Enlightenment? is an American pale ale crafted with Simcoe and Amarillo hops. We aged a small portion of freshly brewed beer in a variety of French oak barrels for over 8 months, dry-hopped with Simcoe and Amarillo and then bottle conditioned. The result: a bright, enlivening and aromatic beer that dares one to be wise and seek reason.

beers.name: Green Street
beers.description: Collaboration with Other Half Brewery, dry hopped with Simcoe hops, El Dorado hops, and Azacca Hops.

beers.name: Double Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: Our good friends @trilliumbrewing let us take a crack at this classic brew for Freaky Friday! This is their description of the beer: Our signature American pale ale balances light, crisp, malt character with an abundance of hop-derived aromatics and flavors from the use of Citra and Columbus. The fragrant nose is fresh citrus, tropical fruit, and peach. Bold flavors of pineapple and mango mix with dank notes of zesty citrus and fresh pine needles. With the smooth mouthfeel, gentle bitterness, and dry finish, Fort Point is our standard daily-drinker.

beers.name: Mosaic Single Hop Pale Ale
beers.description: Single Hop Pale Ale bittered, flavored, and dry-hopped exclusively with Mosaic hops.

beers.name: Citra Single Hop Pale Ale
beers.description: Single hop pale ale bittered, flavored and dry-hopped exclusively with Citra hops.

beers.name: TDH Juice Lee
beers.description: TDH verion of our original collab with Cellarmaker. Triple dry hopped with Nelson Sauvin, Citra, and Motueka

beers.name: 4XDH Envie
beers.description: Enive dry hopped with exactly 4 times the quantity of Citra used in our original recipe.

beers.name: Galaxy Double Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: This special version of our signature American Pale Ale features a double dose of pungent Australian Galaxy in the dry hop. Yellow straw in appearance with a creamy haze and fluffy white head, DDH Galaxy Fort Point exhibits wonderful aromatics of ripe pineapple, bright orange peel, and mango with elegant floral highlights. The palate develops upon the nose with layers of tropical papaya, peach rings, and pulpy citrus adding depth. With the familiar subtle bready malt character and medium body of our Fort Point series, DDH Galaxy FPPA offers a light and satisfying floral tingle on the finish.

beers.name: Intensely Juicy, Dank, Beautiful (Copy & Paste)
beers.description: Pale Ale. 5.9% Collaboration with Hill Farmstead Brewery. Brewed with oats and a tiny bit of caramel malt. Hopped at an outrageous rate (~8lbs/bbl) with Crystal, Amarillo, Simcoe and Galaxy. How much is enough. Where does the inspiration come from?.-Notes of blueberries, grapefruit flesh, blue spruce, and everlasting friendship

beers.name: Mosaic Dry Hop Pseudo Sue
beers.description: This double hop pale ale showcases the Citra and mosaic hop for a well balanced beer that is delicate in body with a mild bitterness in the finish. Ferocious hop aromas of citrus and mango give a refreshing taste that is bright with just enough bite!

beers.name: Double Dry Hopped Envie w/ Citra
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Edward
beers.description: Edward (1917-2002) is our grandfather; Hill Farmstead Brewery rests upon the land that was once home to him and his five children. In his honor, this American Pale Ale is dutifully crafted from American malted barley, a plethora of American hops, our ale yeast and water from Edward’s well. It is unfiltered and dry hopped. Aromatic and flowery, with impressions of citrus and pine, this is the ale that I dream to have shared with Edward. Pale and Caramel malt; Centennial, Chinook, Columbus, Simcoe, and Warrior hops; House Ale Yeast, and our Well Water.

beers.name: Curiosity Twenty Six
beers.description: The 26th installment of our Curiosity Series is an American Pale Ale featuring primarily El Dorado with a splash of Citra hops! Curiosity 26 is built on a sturdy malt base of 2-row, carafoam, and medium crystal providing a deep orange hue and a solid backbone to a supremely hop saturated pale ale! The aroma is potent and citrusy, leading our palates to flavors of orange, mango, and a mixed bouquet tropical fruit. The finish dissolves in a soft mouthfeel and rounded pithy bitterness, vanishing quickly from the pallet and priming the next sip. A real crusher of a Curiosity, indeed!

beers.name: Lights On
beers.description: A modern American Pale Ale brewed to celebrate new beginnings in life, and in creative endeavor! Lights On pours a gorgeous hazy orange in the glass, releasing an aroma filled with a bounty of sweet fresh citrus fruit. We taste papaya, guava, and mango - a fresh and distinctive flavor profile that’s wholly Tree House. Buoyed by a soft and fluffy mouthfeel, Lights On is everything we love in an American Pale Ale.

beers.name: Nelson Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: This new version of our signature American pale ale is dry hopped with Nelson Sauvin hops. Enticingly hazy and blonde in appearance, the nose erupts with aromatics of lime zest, grape jam, and white peach. Flavors of tart citrus, white grape juice and stonefruit permeate the palate, balanced by a soft mouthfeel and dry finish.

beers.name: Zombie Dust
beers.description: This intensely hopped and gushing undead Pale Ale will be one’s only respite after the zombie apocalypse. Created with our marvelous friends in the comic industry.

beers.name: Curiosity Twenty Four
beers.description: Columbus & Citra Hopped Pale similar to Eureka for which it shares many attributes

beers.name: Galaxy Dry Hop Pseudo Sue
beers.description: Forged from the raw elements of the universe, this beer’s hoppy flavor comes from the celestial alignment of both Galaxy and Citra hops. Galaxy dry hopped Pseudo Sue dwarfs all other pale ales.

beers.name: Galaxy Single Hop Pale Ale
beers.description: Single Hop Pale Ale bittered, flavored, and dry-hopped exclusively with Galaxy hops.

beers.name: Enigma Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: This progressive variation of Fort Point Pale Ale spotlights Enigma; a dynamic hop recently developed and cultivated in Australia. Engaging aromas of melon and stone fruit converge on the nose with an intriguing herbal essence in the backdrop. Ripe cantaloupe advances to the palate giving way to complementing flavors of light tropical fruit, blood orange, and a hint of spice. Enigma Dry Hopped Fort Point is medium in body with the distinctively mellow bitterness, gentle mouthfeel, and dry finish of our signature pale ale.

beers.name: Nelson Sauvin Single Hop Pale Ale
beers.description: Single Hop Pale Ale bittered, flavored, and dry-hopped exclusively with Nelson Sauvin hops.

beers.name: Fort Point
beers.description: Our signature American pale ale balances light, crisp, malt character with an abundance of hop-derived aromatics and flavors from the use of Citra and Columbus. The fragrant nose is fresh citrus, tropical fruit, and peach. Bold flavors of pineapple and mango mix with dank notes of zesty citrus and fresh pine needles. With the smooth mouthfeel, gentle bitterness, and dry finish, Fort Point is our standard daily-drinker.

beers.name: Nelson Single Hop Pale Ale
beers.description: American Pale Ale brewed with the same proprietary blend of organically grown malt used in this most recent batch of Edward, and bittered, flavored, and dry-hopped exclusively with a personally selected blend of Nelson Sauvin hops from the 2020 harvest, grown and pelletized by our agricultural partners at Freestyle Hops in Upper Moutere, New Zealand.

beers.name: Sumner
beers.description: American Pale Ale brewed with Simcoe®, Citra®, and Mosaic hops.

beers.name: Conduct of Life
beers.description: An American Pale Ale featuring Citra and Amarillo hops.

beers.name: Barrel-Aged What Is Enlightenment (Batch 3)
beers.description: Originally brewed to celebrate our second anniversary, What is Enlightenment? is an American pale ale crafted with Amarillo® and Simcoe® hops. We aged a small portion of freshly brewed beer in a variety of French oak barrels for over 8 months, dry-hopped with Amarillo® and Simcoe® and then bottle conditioned. The result: a bright, enlivening, and aromatic beer that dares one to be wise and seek reason.

beers.name: Karma Emulsion
beers.description: American Pale Ale brewed with Amarillo®, Centennial, Chinook, and Simcoe® hops.Our friend Jean from Tired Hands Brewing in Ardmore, Pa., made his return to our home and brewdeck in June of 2016 for a few days of brewing. One of the results was Karma Emulsion, a crisp American pale ale—think HopHands meets Edward.

beers.name: Grade 10 W/ Mango
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: What Is Enlightenment?
beers.description: American Pale Ale brewed in honor of our Second Anniversary. Simcoe and Amarillo hops.

beers.name: Xhops Pink
beers.description: X-Hops pink brings tropical fruit flavors of citrus and pineapple, hints of Bubblegum, and a slight pine finish to the palette that leaves you wanting more!

beers.name: Intensely Juicy, Dank, Beautiful (Copy & Paste) w/ Galaxy, Simcoe, and Mosaic
beers.description: Intensely Juicy Dank Beautiful (COPY & PASTE) was originally dreamt up with our great friend Shaun Hill of Hill Farmstead. Designed to recreate a classic-ish American Pale Ale (or is it an IPA?!?) with a few modern twists like oats and hops... lots of modern hops. This batch was foolishly hopped and dry hopped with Galaxy, Simcoe, and Mosaic at the silly rate of 8lbs per barrel. Why do we do this? Where does inspiration come from? How are you?

beers.name: Xhops - Gold
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Lights Out
beers.description: We are excited - and filled with nostalgia - to welcome back Lights Out - a delicious pale ale and an important part of our history! Lights Out pushes the concept of what an American Pale Ale can be. It is exceedingly well hopped at all stages of the brewing process producing a beer that is both intense yet still classically balanced. The prevailing flavor is tangerine - even lingering pleasantly in the finish - with heaps of pungent grapefruit and citrus rind contributing to the complexity of this little delight. We find it to be a joy to drink all the way through the glass. Lights Out is the very first beer we canned. As we embark on new projects it reminds us of a very important and creative period in our history and energizes us for what is to come.

beers.name: Double Dry Hopped Envie
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Juice Lee
beers.description: Juice Lee - our collaborative Pale Ale with the pale-ale-loving and masters-of-pun Cellarmaker. 6.0% ABV pale ale with good amounts of Vienna malt and hopped in kung-fu balance with danky Nelson hops and fruity Citra and Motueka. A lovely, balanced, and crushable Pale Ale.

beers.name: Motueka Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: This version of our signature American pale ale is dry hopped with Motueka. Hazy and blonde in appearance, the nose conjures melon, lemon drops and pineapple aromatics. Robust hop flavors of cantaloupe and fresh cut grass are balanced by a subtle, bready malt character and mild, subdued bitterness.

beers.name: Late Harvest Nelson Pale Ale
beers.description: American Pale Ale brewed with late harvested Nelson Sauvin hops from New Zealand. Released on 03/20/2019

beers.name: Xhops Gold (2021)
beers.description: Amped up with an electric selection of hops and a sunburst color that would give Les Paul all the vibes; X-Hops Gold is a melodic blend of Strata, Citra, Simcoe, and Sabro hops. This super-saturated haze for dayz shredder has really struck a chord with us. Rock on.

beers.name: Barrel-Aged What Is Enlightenment? (Batch 2)
beers.description: Originally brewed to celebrate our second anniversary, What is Enlightenment? is an American pale ale crafted with Simcoe® and Amarillo® hops. We aged a small portion of freshly brewed beer in a variety of French oak barrels for over 8 months, dry-hopped with Simcoe® and Amarillo® and then bottle conditioned. The result: a bright, enlivening and aromatic beer that dares one to be wise and seek reason.

beers.name: Lush Land
beers.description: Lush Land is a juicy, aromatic pale ale brewed with a large percentage of malted oats and generously dry hopped with mosaic and comet.

beers.name: Skimpy Sparrow
beers.description: An easy drinking hoppy American pale ale, Skimpy Sparrow is another edition in our "Small Bird Series" of lower ABV offerings brewed for the summer. The nose is an intense, complex fusion of pineapple, grapefruit pith, and woodsy hop aromatics. Citrus rind, grape jam, and lemon fill out the flavor profile, with a firm and long-lasting bitterness. Very dry and effervescent, light to medium bodied.

beers.name: Galactic Double Daisy Cutter
beers.description: Galactic Double Daisy Cutter is the amplified version of our stalwart pale, skinned with the tropical impact of Galaxy hops.

beers.name: Juli-ish
beers.description: Juli-ish was an inevitability for hot summer days. Crafted to be everything you love about Julius, but in a pale ale form! Juli-ish carries a glowing orange body and a uniquely fluffy appeal. Juli-ish oozes with notes of fresh-squeezed orange juice, sticky mango, and tropical fruit offset by an appropriate and thirst-quenching bitterness. Pale Ale nirvana!

beers.name: Pier
beers.description: Brewed with 30% wheat, this hoppy, golden American ale features Galaxy and Citra in the dry hop. Bright aromatics of overripe peach, orange rind, and green, herbal hops flood the nose while balanced flavors of tropical fruit, citrus, and creamy wheat excite the palate. Refreshingly light bodied with a soft, fluffy mouthfeel, Pier finishes dry with a slightly mineral bitterness.

beers.name: Simcoe® Single Hop Pale Ale
beers.description: Single Hop Pale Ale bittered, flavored, and dry-hopped exclusively with Simcoe® hops.

beers.name: Riwaka Double Daisy Cutter
beers.description: We add the Riwaka hop to our very small list of Double Daisy Cutter variants, a hop very deserving of full focus in a bigger version of our classic pale ale.Powerfully present, a diesel Daisy sorbet twist cone with a cotton candy coating.

beers.name: Mosaic Double Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: Mosaic Double Dry Hopped Fort Point offers everything we've come to love from the aptly-named Pacific Northwest varietal. A blend of pineapple juice, mango gelato, and passion fruit notes are exhibited by one of our most captivating hoppy offerings to date.

beers.name: Vic Secret Dry Hopped Fort Point
beers.description: This dry hopped pale ale contains the same malt bill as classic Fort Point, but with a dry hop of Vic Secret. Pouring a hazy golden color, Vic Secret Fort Point emits herbaceous aromas of lime, and mellow citrus. Strong grapefruit pith & biscuity flavors wash the palate with the familiar smooth mouthfeel and medium body of our signature pale ale.

beers.name: Plucky
beers.description: Plucky is made (almost entirely) with Simpsons Golden Promise malt, our favorite pub ale yeast strain and a blend of hops that undoubtedly drives the personality of this beer. That combo leans heavily on late-boil additions of UK-grown Brambling Cross and Fuggles whole leaf hops - neither have proven easy to find stateside but a direct shipment from the UK helped bring Plucky to life. Everything here is understated and best enjoyed by the pint without a fuss but if we had to describe it, the malt is lightly sweet and nutty and those lovely hops are throwing subtle dark fruit, orange marmalade and black tea.

beers.name: Cuppa
beers.description: Cuppa is a British Ale blended with cold-brew coffee, sourced from our friends at Broadsheet Coffee Roasters (Somerville, MA). Single origin Peruvian “Flor de Selva” beans lend flavors of dark chocolate, cola, and ripe cherry to a mild and biscuity base. Cheers to uppers and downers!

beers.name: Appropriate Alchemy
beers.description: Brewed with British Golden Promise and hopped with lots of American Strata. It has notes of citrus marmalade on fresh biscuits, orange meringue, classic British malt flavors, and an ethereally balanced finish. The kind of beautifully simple beer we love so much.

beers.name: Sonorous
beers.description: English summer ale

beers.name: Engrailed
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Vujà Dé: Landlord
beers.description: Vujà Dé is when you look at something familiar in a new way, so that's what we've called our new series of modern interpretations on classic beers, with Landlord paying homage to Timothy Taylor Landlord as the quintessential English Pale Ale. Landlord seeks to capture that classic English Pale Ale experience, but with American ingredients.

beers.name: Breakfast of Thrones
beers.description: Breakfast of Thrones hits your mug with a nice blue-ish amber hue.Strong aromas of blueberries and maple syrup on a behemoth stack of waffles. We used a nice blend of biscuit and specialty malts to give that cake batter mouthfeel while you bite into your breakfast. Hits the tongue like a squirting blueberry with drizzles of sticky maple syrup and vanilla to pleasure the mouth. So why don't you sit on your Throne, devour your morgenmete and raise a glass to the King of the North!

beers.name: White Arrow Pine Ale
beers.description: This beer was brewed with over 10 lbs of locally picked pine sprigs. The essence of pine is strong without being overwhelming.

beers.name: Mahogany & Rosewood
beers.description: This English-style pale ale was brewed with the finest continental ingredients available to create a flavorful and balanced sessionable pub ale. In collaboration with our pals at Stick City Brewing Co.

beers.name: ESB
beers.description: Our take on this classic English pale ale pours a beautiful orange-copper with a fluffy white head. Bitter by name, balanced in style.

beers.name: Pub Ale
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Tessy's Pale Ale
beers.description: A crisp, hoppy west-coast style pale ale-- perfect for the summer.

beers.name: So Many Promises
beers.description: An English Pale Ale collaboration with our friends at Berryessa Brewing Co. It’s no secret that both of our breweries love traditional English styles and we also share admiration for Landlord Pale Ale from Timothy Taylor. ⠀⠀So when it came time for us to collab it was kind of a no-brainer and thus we present to you So Many Promises. This beer features 100% Simpsons Golden Promise (@simpsonsmalt) malted barley and Styrian Golding hops for a classic English Pale that’s malty, fruity and spicy.

beers.name: Strictly Speaking
beers.description: Manchester-style Hoppy Cask Pale Ale w/ Strata. Collab w/ TrackOur collab with our buds from Manchester, UK was inspired by a beer of theirs that we fell in love with during our visits out that way. So they shared all their secrets, their recipe, their technique, and then we riffed it from there. It’s a modern British Pale Ale that gets heavily hopped and kept a bit hazy, but still maintains the strength and drinkability of the pub ales that have inspired it. The beer is medium in body, hazy pale in color, and it hits with some strawberry jam on toast kinda vibes (thank you Strata!), has a pleasant herbal quality, and then finishes with that moreish quality that we were hoping for.

beers.name: Burton Haze
beers.description: English-Style Hazy Pale AleShow Less

beers.name: Unfiltered DBA (Double Barrel Ale)
beers.description: Our flagship brew highlights barrel-fermented batches from our patented Firestone Union blended with beer fermented in stainless steel. It opens with a biscuity toasted malt aroma and a hint of oak and vanilla. Pale malts create a smooth malty middle with ribbons of caramel, English toffee and toasted oak. A tribute to English pales traditionally fermented in cask.Show Less

beers.name: Royal Scandal, Dry Hopped
beers.description: Always a crowd pleaser, our version of the ever popular Pale Ale leans more towards an English Bitter than the everyday American Pale Ale. Earthy on the nose with a light floral background, this brew has a lingering caramel malt flavor and a splash of fresh citrus. The chosen yeast strain provides a distinctly European feel, but our hop profile remains uniquely American in delivering the expected flavor and aroma, as well as a characteristic bitter edge. It is hop-forward with a balance towards late hop additions and bitterness, yet this medium-bodied brew maintains an ample malt foundation on the way to a smooth, refreshing finish.

beers.name: Temporalis
beers.description: Heavily dry hopped with Chinook, Mosaic, and Hallertau Blanc. Notes of light pine, clementines, unripe pears, papaya, vanilla.

beers.name: Cracks in the Pyre
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Shamanic Whip VI: Quantum of Solace
beers.description: Golden, zesty, tangerine, and floral notes. The finest Northwest-grown, British-origin hops to create a balance of herbal citrus and bright, earthy fruits. British-grown Marris Otter and Golden Promise create a base of soft bread coupled with a classic British ale yeast strain for a restrained ester profile. Easy drinking and unfathomably refreshing.

beers.name: Secret Menu Item
beers.description: Hopped with Brewers Gold

beers.name: Pelican's Own Pale Ale
beers.description: Sold only at Pelican Inn near Muir Beach.

beers.name: Fuggarillo
beers.description: Amarillo & Fuggle-hopped English Pale Ale

beers.name: A Hoppier Shade of Pale
beers.description: West Coast Pale with English roots. We used English malt and our house yeast to make this beer stand out as a balanced and unique addition to the hoppy pale landscape. It has a strong grapefruit and citrus aroma, with smooth malty flavor and body. The name is a nod to the classic Procol Harum song.

beers.name: Make It Dangerous
beers.description: The Homies from Calusa Brewing came up to make things dangerous with us and brew this English Pale ale fermented on ex-bourbon barrel staves.

beers.name: The Best Beer Brewed In All of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania Thus Far In All of American History
beers.description: Collaboration with Bonn Place Brewing Company

beers.name: Heritage Pale Ale
beers.description: Single malt.

beers.name: Garden of England
beers.description: English Pale Ale with EKG Hops

beers.name: Wax & Wane
beers.description: Pale gold, with a creamy off-white head, the soft bready malt makes sure you know it's there, balanced by a notably earthy, floral hop presence. Like so many of our beers, it's the kind you'll most likely want to have more than one of... Make sure to grab some fresh and see for yourself!

beers.name: Well Chuffed
beers.description: The color of freshly polished brass bar rails and as inviting as an everyday butler, innit? This new brew will have you calling up your mates totally gobsmacked. Cheers!

beers.name: Maas Primo
beers.description: A slightly toasty little pale ale with notes of floral herbs, cracker and orange marmalade. Hopped with 100% UK Fuggle, UK malt and yeast.

beers.name: Monka Coffee Ale
beers.description: Coffee infused light ale. Guessing on the style

beers.name: Ilk
beers.description: Ordinary pale beer. A beer of English nature, ilk is a tangent of the hop forward, perplexingly malty, yet yeast driven ales of Yorkshire. Just Golden Promise, just East Kent Goldings, and a quirky yeast known for bouncing off the walls of square shaped vessels. This abridged combination of ingredients renders a beer with tones of orange marmalade and apricot jam on white toast. Drinkable and thinkable.

beers.name: At Her Majesty's Pleasure
beers.description: English Style End of Summer Ale Featuring Nelson Sauvin Hops, coriander, and orange peel.

beers.name: Willamette Pale
beers.description: This single malt/single hop beer is a collaboration with Bryan Keilty of Gorges Brewing. We partnered with Skagit Valley malt and used a variety called Pilot Dark, lending the beer a nice amber hue. The kettle was loaded with willamette hops, then we open fermented it with our house ale yeast. This one drinks like a classic from the U.K. with big but balanced flavors and plenty of nuance despite a modest abv of only 4.3%.

beers.name: Royal Scandal
beers.description: Always a crowd pleaser, our version of the ever popular Pale Ale leans more towards an English Bitter than the everyday American Pale Ale. Earthy on the nose with a light floral background, this brew has a lingering caramel malt flavor and a splash of fresh citrus. The chosen yeast strain provides a distinctly European feel, but our hop profile remains uniquely American in delivering the expected flavor and aroma, as well as a characteristic bitter edge. It is hop-forward with a balance towards late hop additions and bitterness, yet this medium-bodied brew maintains an ample malt foundation on the way to a smooth, refreshing finish.

beers.name: Only Yesterday
beers.description: Our first pub ale in cans, Only Yesterday is a nod to ales that have been enjoyed in English pubs over the centuries. It's brewed with a base of Simpsons UK malts including Golden Promise and a touch of Double Roasted Crystal, as well as English East Kent Golding hops. Amber-orange in color with an off-white head, this beer imparts aromas of caramelized pear, biscuits and red apple that accompany notes of black tea, freshly baked bread and pear on the tongue. Best consumed at cellar temperature to get the full flavor of the beer, a pint of this one will transport your senses into the English pubs of yesteryear.

beers.name: Old Piney Pub Ale
beers.description: Hand Pump Pub Ale

beers.name: Pub Ale
beers.description: Malty & barley Pub Ale

beers.name: Troll Serum
beers.description: Lactose Pale Ale cask-condtioned on Whole Leaf Simcoe hops and Brussels Brett from The Yeast Bay

beers.name: Amarillo Extra Pale
beers.description: This extra pale was brewed with pilsner malt, wheat, 2-row barley, and hopped exclusively with Amarillo. It was then fermented with one of our favorite Ebglish strains and dry-hopped with more Amarillo.

beers.name: Zed Word
beers.description: England’s finest Maris Otter malt and signature East Kent Golding hops star in this flavor picture written and directed by HenHouse for your tongue to enjoy! The Zed Word’s copper color foreshadows the malty flavors in the glass. Nutty notes of toast and caramel partner with dark fruit flavors and lower hop bitterness unite to form an ale so properly British; if you listen to your glass, you could hear the bubbles murmur “God Save The Queen”!

beers.name: Summer
beers.description: In 1792, George Hodgson opened the Bow Brewery in London’s East End. Hodgson sold Pale Ale successfully for years, including sales to India’s British colonists. Burton brewers began producing large amounts of Pale Ale as well and became very well known for the quality. Our Summer Pale Ale is light gold in color and of moderate strength. Like British Pale Ales, ours is filtered, fully carbonated, and a slightly stronger version of a premium bitter.Show Less

beers.name: SoHo, London Pub Ale
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Unfiltered Hoppy Digital Nitro
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Deep Ascent Pale Ale
beers.description: In the summer of 2017, Long Island Divers recovered various bottles from a shipwreck just off of Long Island's southern beaches. The divers were atop the Oregon, a well known Transatlantic luxury liner that met her demise in 1886. Diver/brewer Jamie Adams of Saint James Brewery, Holbrook, Long Island, immediately set about reinvigorating near 130 years old beer yeast culture, found at the bottom of the hand blown glass bottles, into viable yeast cultures able to make beer. The result of his extensive efforts is Deep Ascent New York Pale Ale. Deep Ascentis brewed as a single yeast fermentation Ale using only our "dynamo" ship wreck yeast procured from the shipwreck Oregon. This is the first time we are brewing solely with the Dynamo yeast on its own, not a mixed fermentation. Enjoy

beers.name: Zoodog
beers.description: Pale Ale with Elderflower

beers.name: Cervus
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Country Mile
beers.description: A honey hued golden ale with a full body and maximum quafability. Expect notes of rich nutty malt, dried fruit and hints of honey.

beers.name: Double Fantasy: Nelson
beers.description: Double pale ale brewed with Two-row, Oats and Wheat and hopped exclusively with Nelson and Nelson CGX @crosbyhops.

beers.name: Calamansi
beers.description: Brett Pale Aged in Oak with Calamansi Limes, Tanzanian & Madagascar Vanilla and Toasted CoconutA foray into further experimentation of exotic fruit usage paired with thoughtful additions of vanilla and toasted coconut. This blend was inspired by our previous La Belle Fleur fruited variants.

beers.name: Bastron
beers.description: Meet Bastron, a pale ale designed to maximize the presence of thiols: small but mightily aromatic organic compounds found in hop cones.Experimentation with a new yeast strain called Star Party led us to this recipe, hopped methodically with a blend catered towards the yeast itself to highlight alllll the drippy, tropical fruit-forward notes there are to find.

beers.name: 10 Year Anniversary Pale Ale
beers.description: Hazy West Coast Pale Ale hopped with HBC 586, Citra Cryo and @freestylehops Nelson Sauvin SubZero Hop Kief which is a distillate of Nelson hop oils.

beers.name: Duality: Nelson & Strata
beers.description: The first in a series of 2-Hop pale ales exploring the sexiest hops the world has to offer. There couldn’t be a better combo to start with than New Zealand Nelson Sauvin and American Strata – possibly each hemisphere’s version of the other. Both have amazing white wine notes coupled with tropical mango and pineapple. Hints of strawberry also poke out behind the punchier fruit and marijuana-like tanginess.

beers.name: Kushy Clouds
beers.description: Kushy Clouds is an extremely juicy and fluffy Oatmeal Pale Ale. Brewed with a hefty addition of rolled oats and pilsner malt, then dry hopped with out favorite blend of citrus and pineapple forward hops.

beers.name: Spelty Boys
beers.description: Spelt Pale Ale Hopped with Southern Cross and Vista Can Release 4/20/24 $17/4 packWe swapped the wheat malt in our usual pale ale recipe for spelt. It's a high-protein cousin to wheat that adds body and a slightly rustic graininess. We leaned into that with Southern Cross, a New Zealand variety with apricot and spicy pine. Balanced by the tropical fruit and peach of American Vista.

beers.name: Enthusiasm Uncurbed
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Duality: Riwaka & Simcoe
beers.description: The second in a series of 2-Hop pale ales exploring the sexiest hops the world has to offer. This round brings together the elusive and tantalizing New Zealand grown Riwaka with our favorite American grown hop, Simcoe. This elegant and unassuming beer is soft and floral with hints of cantaloupe, satsuma mandarin flesh and subtle peach nectar.

beers.name: Drink It In
beers.description: When we decided to bring some So Cal love with us up to San Francisco Beer Week this year, teaming up with Societe Brewing Company in San Diego was a no brainer. We settled on brewing up a BIG Pale Ale, and in the process stretched the style so far beyond its limits that we decided to call it something else entirely. We present a San Diego Style Pale Ale. It is light bodied, crisp and drinkable- but assertively hop forward at the same time. We loaded it up with Simcoe, Centennial and Idaho 7 hops and were rewarded with a cloud of pink grapefruit, bitter orange, pine, and fresh herbs that lingers above the glass. In the sip, supporting notes of berries, melon and citrus hold on into the clean finish that just disappears on you, and pulls you back in for more.

beers.name: Woodlet
beers.description: Show Less

beers.name: Front Porch Swing
beers.description: Pale Ale with Peach TeaCan Release 4/20/24 - $18/4 packThis beer was inspired by the feeling of sitting on a front porch swing in summer, sipping peach-flavored ice tea. We leaned into the underlying peach and apricot aromatics of the hops (Vista and Southern Cross) with a delicate addition of peach-flavored tea. The tea itself adds herbal notes helping to balance the fruity aromatics. The finish balances the sweetness of the pale malt, juiciness of the hops, and richness of the tea leaves.

beers.name: Quietly Open In Raleigh
beers.description: For our first ever pale ale, we’re tossing in some of our favorite hop varieties. Pacific Sunrise, El Dorado, and Idaho 7 lend a modern touch to a classic style and bring notes of melon, pineapple, and red berry. A generous mash addition of malted oats helps soften up the body. Cheers to quietly opening up the doors in the City of Oaks!

beers.name: Watch For Falling Coconuts
beers.description: Citra, El Dorado & Sabro-hopped American Pale Ale Brewed With CoconutDraft version is 6.5%

beers.name: ECHOLALIA
beers.description: WEST COAST PALE ALE WITH CITRA AND SIMCOE

beers.name: Conservas
beers.description: We go way back with our friends at Cabon Copy, Kyle and Brendon. We also share a love of tinned fish and colorful Portuguese tins. If that doesn't scream pale ale then maybe this delicious combo of Nectaron and NZ Cascade will. Expect some lime zest, sweet pineapple, peach and a touch of dank from this tasty hop duo.Show Less

beers.name: Blonde Roast
beers.description: English Pale Ale with Coffee and Orange ZestCan Release 4/29 - $16/4-packThere are thousands of coffee stouts and porters out there. Roasted malt and roasted coffee is a delicious combination, but sometimes we want a beer that shows off the varietal notes of a coffee without over-accentuating the roast. This beer pairs a light-roast coffee with a twist of orange zest. The fresh fruit and light hopping accentuate the citrusy coffee rather than the char for a coffee beer that is down-right refreshing!

beers.name: Nelson Weekdayer
beers.description: Nelson Weekdayer is an all-Nelson Pale Ale to enjoy on any day of the week, at home, or at your favorite spot. What else could you ask for?

beers.name: Danger of Blue Light
beers.description: Extra Pale Ale with Freeze Dried Blueberries, and Lemon VerbenaCan Release 10/8 - $19Mosaic hops provide a berry-citrus aroma on their own. So we added real freeze-dried blueberries to enhance the blueberry impression along with a bright lemondrop candy note of homegrown lemon verbena. The hibiscus reinforces both the berry color and aroma! Combined it's still more hoppy beer than fruit beer, but with an exaggerated fruit impression

beers.name: The Kenyan
beers.description: Coffee Pale Ale

beers.name: Young'uns
beers.description: Euro Style pale ale. Hopped with German Hersbrucker, experimental hops, and small flourishes of citrusy USA grown hop varietals. Fermented cold with our house ale yeast and cold-conditioned for a short spell.

beers.name: Flowers of the Sky – Fresh Hop Hazy Pale Ale (2023)
beers.description: Flowers of the Sky is our fresh hop hazy pale ale brewed with a base of pilsner malt, flaked oats and flaked barley. We hopped Flowers of the Sky with Strata, Comet and Galaxy in the kettle and fermented it with our house kölsch strain. Flowers of the Sky was then dry hopped with more Stata, Comet and Galaxy, and finally cold-infused with an insane amount of fresh Strata hops from Crosby Hop Farm.

beers.name: Tēnā Koutou
beers.description: Tena Koutou is a mixed-fermentationPale Ale with a delightful blend of flavors, aromas, and textures that will transport your senses straight to the beautiful landscapes of New Zealand.Brewed with a famous duo of New Zealand hops, Nelson Sauvin and Motekd, and fermented with our mixed-fermentation culture, it pout S light orange hue with a fully white Read, Tropical agomar of white wins, gooseberries, passionfruit, and lime exude from the glass, accompanied by a mild funk in the background.Tena Koutou showcases the best of New Zealand's hop varietles, aftellig a complex and enjoyable drinking. experience perfect for a warm summer day or a relaxing evening with friends, Cheers!

beers.name: Freezy Poofs
beers.description: Cryo-Hopped Pale Ale

beers.name: Just A Phase- Mosaic Pale Ale
beers.description: We'd like to introduce the newest series from the Milwaukee brewery: Just a Phase. Featuring different hops in each batch, this first release will feature everyone's favorite, Mosaic hops. Mosaic brings tropical fruit aromas of passion fruit, and adds in some earthy-floral complexity reminiscent of blueberry and peach, and finishes with a citrusy lime & tangerine, keeping things bright.

beers.name: Quasi Projects
beers.description: Quasi Projects arise from our dreams. They start in the Other and slowly work themselves into the reality of our everyday lives. An idea for a beer can start in our minds eye, then can be brought to fruition through our work in the brewhouse. Quasi Projects, once just a thought, is now a real German Pale Ale hopped with an unprecedented 14 different hops! Pungent and dank with notes of light spice, lemon, evergreen resins, and a touch of white grape, this Pale Ale is easy, soft and delicious. Enjoy one or two and see what types of Quasi Projects you can make real!

beers.name: Seattle Beer Week 14 Hoppy Pale
beers.description: We were honored to be asked to brew this hop forward, easy drinking pale ale as the official beer for Seattle Beer Week 14. We kept the ABV moderate and the hop additions bright for a beer that will fuel the party all week long. Mosaic, Citra, HBC 586 and Simcoe pack aromas and flavor of citrus, berry and mango. Happy Beer Week, Seattle!

beers.name: Flippin' Delicious
beers.description: Billed as an "International Pale Ale" that features lighter body with less caramel malt notes and utilizes German Saphir, Mandarina Bavaria, and Austrian Galaxy hops.

beers.name: Foggy Recall
beers.description: A decadently hopped pale ale packed with oats for a silky texture and featuring Citra, Mosaic, Galaxy, Nelson Sauvin, Centennial, and experimental hop HBC 1019.

beers.name: Pivot

beers.name: Pacer
beers.description: We brewed this pale ale with hand-foraged Maine spruce tips to celebrate the annual Millinocket Marathon & Half: an impactful free race held each year to support local businesses in Maine’s most legendary mill town. As our team of runners grows each year, we wanted to do our part. $3500 from this beer will be donated to the Stearns High School Scholarship Fund, a scholarship Bissell Brothers helped kick off in 2022 to support the Town of Millinocket’s desire to encourage a graduating senior from their community.

beers.name: Suburban Transit
beers.description: For this bright little number we brewed a Pale Ale with ties to our favorite things about west coast and east coast hoppy beers. A hybrid if you will. Bursting with rays of pineapple sunshine and grapefruit zest and followed with a gentle, tropical finish. This is one you can enjoy all day long!

beers.name: Mando Mango
beers.description: Pale Ale with Freeze Dried Mangoes and TerpenesCan Release 5/18 - $18/4-packWe're sponsoring our first Disc Golf tournament this year, Sapwood Showdown May 25-26, 2024 at Patapsco Valley State Park! We decided to rely on our brewer (and resident disc golfer) Joe for a suggestion of what style would go over well with discgolfistas, he went with the "synergistic" combination of mangoes and terpenes on a mango-forward Simcoe pale ale base. Fruity, dank, and crushable!

beers.name: Mimosa or Pale?
beers.description: Mimosa or Pale is a ProAm beer we made with our friends at Mount Olympus Brewing out of Montesano WA. This not-so-traditional take on a "historic Cream Ale" is brewed with corn grits and Pilsner malt to an ABV of 5.2% with a low bitterness. The true-to-style stops there as we dry hopped the beer with DIPA quantities of Citra and Galaxy and fermented it out with our favorite Juicy yeast strain, leading to the question; Mimosa or Pale Ale?Show Less
